{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014dE8wf1KQSNc1RYVrYeiuc","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Comprehensive Report:\n\n1. Directory Structure:\n   - Root structure is a Maven-based Java project\n   - Key directories:\n     * src/main/java: Main source code\n     * src/main/resources: Configuration files\n     * src/test/java: Test files\n     * .mvn: Maven wrapper\n     * e2e: End-to-end test scripts\n\n2. Build System:\n   - Maven (pom.xml)\n   - Quarkus 3.30.5 framework\n   - Java 21 (maven.compiler.release set to 21)\n   - Key dependencies:\n     * Quarkus REST Jackson\n     * PostgreSQL JDBC\n     * Hibernate ORM Panache\n     * SmallRye JWT\n     * Hibernate Validator\n   - Plugins:\n     * Quarkus Maven Plugin\n     * Spotless for code formatting\n     * Surefire for testing\n\n3. Java Source Packages:\n   Main package: org.example.realworldapi\n   Key subpackages:\n   - application.web: Web resources and models\n   - domain.feature: Business logic implementations\n   - domain.model: Domain models\n   - domain.exception: Custom exceptions\n   - infrastructure: Configurations and providers\n\n4. Configuration:\n   - application.properties highlights:\n     * REST API base path: /api\n     * PostgreSQL database configuration\n     * JWT key locations and issuer\n     * Hibernate ORM set to drop-and-create database\n\n5. Dockerfile:\n   - Based on Maven 3.9.12 with IBM Semeru JDK 21\n   - Installs additional tools (PostgreSQL, uv, Playwright)\n   - Creates Python virtual environment\n   - Builds application using Maven\n\n6. Test Coverage:\n   - Integration tests for:\n     * Users\n     * Articles\n     * Profiles\n     * Tags\n   - Includes abstract base test classes\n   - Uses JUnit 5 and Rest Assured\n\n7. Framework-Specific Files:\n   - resources-config.json: Likely for resource handling\n   - privateKey.pem and publicKey.pem: JWT key files\n\nThis is a Quarkus-based Jakarta EE application implementing a Real World API, following a clean architecture with clear separation of concerns between web, domain, and infrastructure layers.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of the project?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"436fde86-969f-4ebf-b53f-85d3de40aacd"}
