2→            <li>Configure your application in <code>src/main/resources/application.properties</code>.\n   123→            </li>\n   124→        </ul>\n   125→\n   126→        <h2>How do I get rid of this page?</h2>\n   127→        <p>Just delete the <code>src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/index.html</code> file.</p>\n   128→    </div>\n   129→    <div class=\"right-column\">\n   130→        <div class=\"right-section\">\n   131→            <h3>Application</h3>\n   132→            <ul>\n   133→                <li>GroupId: org.example</li>\n   134→                <li>ArtifactId: realworldapiservice</li>\n   135→                <li>Version: 1.0-SNAPSHOT</li>\n   136→                <li>Quarkus Version: 0.21.1</li>\n   137→            </ul>\n   138→        </div>\n   139→        <div class=\"right-section\">\n   140→            <h3>Next steps</h3>\n   141→            <ul>\n   142→                <li><a href=\"https://quarkus.io/guides/maven-tooling.html\">Setup your IDE</a></li>\n   143→                <li><a href=\"https://quarkus.io/guides/getting-started-guide.html\">Getting started</a></li>\n   144→                <li><a href=\"https://quarkus.io\">Quarkus Web Site</a></li>\n   145→            </ul>\n   146→        </div>\n   147→    </div>\n   148→</div>\n   149→\n   150→\n   151→</body>\n   152→</html>\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016AbnPo8v5goYPE39W2P9B4","session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"10116764-8b0c-4ea1-8919-c63baa32f240"}
