{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014Dw68BCgeqpDgFT7ZzS4cq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.hibernate.orm.panache.PanacheRepositoryBase;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.UUID;\n     6→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.*;\n     9→\n    10→public class AbstractPanacheRepository<ENTITY, ID> implements PanacheRepositoryBase<ENTITY, ID> {\n    11→\n    12→  protected UserEntity findUserEntityById(UUID id) {\n    13→    return getEntityManager().find(UserEntity.class, id);\n    14→  }\n    15→\n    16→  protected TagEntity findTagEntityById(UUID id) {\n    17→    return getEntityManager().find(TagEntity.class, id);\n    18→  }\n    19→\n    20→  protected ArticleEntity findArticleEntityById(UUID id) {\n    21→    return getEntityManager().find(ArticleEntity.class, id);\n    22→  }\n    23→\n    24→  protected CommentEntity findCommentEntityById(UUID id) {\n    25→    return getEntityManager().find(CommentEntity.class, id);\n    26→  }\n    27→\n    28→  protected FavoriteRelationshipEntity findFavoriteRelationshipEntityByKey(\n    29→      FavoriteRelationship favoriteRelationship) {\n    30→\n    31→    final var userEntity = findUserEntityById(favoriteRelationship.getUser().getId());\n    32→    final var articleEntity = findArticleEntityById(favoriteRelationship.getArticle().getId());\n    33→\n    34→    final var favoriteRelationshipEntityKey = new FavoriteRelationshipEntityKey();\n    35→    favoriteRelationshipEntityKey.setUser(userEntity);\n    36→    favoriteRelationshipEntityKey.setArticle(articleEntity);\n    37→\n    38→    return getEntityManager().find(FavoriteRelationshipEntity.class, favoriteRelationshipEntityKey);\n    39→  }\n    40→\n    41→  protected boolean isNotEmpty(List<?> list) {\n    42→    return list != null && !list.isEmpty();\n    43→  }\n    44→\n    45→  protected List<String> toUpperCase(List<String> subjectList) {\n    46→    return subjectList.stream().map(String::toUpperCase).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    47→  }\n    48→}\n    49→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QWH2HE8revLKZ7i4nuJjFP","session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"36a86c47-7f58-4363-b162-4c877a441f27"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DJuRiCR1K2UYiav1FRA1eo","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n     2→\n     3→import static io.quarkus.panache.common.Parameters.with;\n     4→\n     5→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import java.util.Optional;\n     7→import java.util.UUID;\n     8→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.EntityUtils;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.UserEntity;\n    13→\n    14→@ApplicationScoped\n    15→@AllArgsConstructor\n    16→public class UserRepositoryPanache extends AbstractPanacheRepository<UserEntity, UUID>\n    17→    implements UserRepository {\n    18→\n    19→  private final EntityUtils entityUtils;\n    20→\n    21→  @Override\n    22→  public void save(User user) {\n    23→    persist(new UserEntity(user));\n    24→  }\n    25→\n    26→  @Override\n    27→  public boolean existsBy(String field, String value) {\n    28→    return count(\"upper(\" + field + \")\", value.toUpperCase().trim()) > 0;\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  @Override\n    32→  public Optional<User> findByEmail(String email) {\n    33→    return find(\"upper(email)\", email.toUpperCase().trim())\n    34→        .firstResultOptional()\n    35→        .map(entityUtils::user);\n    36→  }\n    37→\n    38→  @Override\n    39→  public Optional<User> findUserById(UUID id) {\n    40→    return findByIdOptional(id).map(entityUtils::user);\n    41→  }\n    42→\n    43→  @Override\n    44→  public boolean existsUsername(UUID excludeId, String username) {\n    45→    return count(\n    46→            \"id != :excludeId and upper(username) = :username\",\n    47→            with(\"excludeId\", excludeId).and(\"username\", username.toUpperCase().trim()))\n    48→        > 0;\n    49→  }\n    50→\n    51→  @Override\n    52→  public boolean existsEmail(UUID excludeId, String email) {\n    53→    return count(\n    54→            \"id != :excludeId and upper(email) = :email\",\n    55→            with(\"excludeId\", excludeId).and(\"email\", email.toUpperCase().trim()))\n    56→        > 0;\n    57→  }\n    58→\n    59→  @Override\n    60→  public void update(User user) {\n    61→    final var userEntity = findById(user.getId());\n    62→    userEntity.update(user);\n    63→  }\n    64→\n    65→  @Override\n    66→  public Optional<User> findByUsername(String username) {\n    67→    return find(\"upper(username)\", username.toUpperCase().trim())\n    68→        .firstResultOptional()\n    69→        .map(entityUtils::user);\n    70→  }\n    71→}\n    72→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QWH2HE8revLKZ7i4nuJjFP","session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"c423a832-2005-4eae-aa83-7c79bae140c1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011XMHzyNPdJ2xCKcuA8XTrv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.panache.common.Page;\n     4→import io.quarkus.panache.common.Parameters;\n     5→import io.quarkus.panache.common.Sort;\n     6→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→import java.util.*;\n     8→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     9→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleFilter;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.PageResult;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.ArticleEntity;\n    15→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.EntityUtils;\n    16→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache.utils.SimpleQueryBuilder;\n    17→\n    18→@ApplicationScoped\n    19→@AllArgsConstructor\n    20→public class ArticleRepositoryPanache extends AbstractPanacheRepository<ArticleEntity, UUID>\n    21→    implements ArticleRepository {\n    22→\n    23→  private final EntityUtils entityUtils;\n    24→\n    25→  @Override\n    26→  public boolean existsBySlug(String slug) {\n    27→    return count(\"upper(slug)\", slug.toUpperCase().trim()) > 0;\n    28→  }\n    29→\n    30→  @Override\n    31→  public void save(Article article) {\n    32→    final var author = findUserEntityById(article.getAuthor().getId());\n    33→    persistAndFlush(new ArticleEntity(article, author));\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  @Override\n    37→  public Optional<Article> findArticleById(UUID id) {\n    38→    return findByIdOptional(id).map(entityUtils::article);\n    39→  }\n    40→\n    41→  @Override\n    42→  public Optional<Article> findBySlug(String slug) {\n    43→    return find(\"upper(slug)\", slug.toUpperCase().trim())\n    44→        .firstResultOptional()\n    45→        .map(entityUtils::article);\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  @Override\n    49→  public void update(Article article) {\n    50→    final var articleEntity = findArticleEntityById(article.getId());\n    51→    articleEntity.update(article);\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  @Override\n    55→  public Optional<Article> findByAuthorAndSlug(UUID authorId, String slug) {\n    56→    return find(\n    57→            \"author.id = :authorId and upper(slug) = :slug\",\n    58→            Parameters.with(\"authorId\", authorId).and(\"slug\", slug.toUpperCase().trim()))\n    59→        .firstResultOptional()\n    60→        .map(entityUtils::article);\n    61→  }\n    62→\n    63→  @Override\n    64→  public void delete(Article article) {\n    65→    deleteById(article.getId());\n    66→  }\n    67→\n    68→  @Override\n    69→  public PageResult<Article> findMostRecentArticlesByFilter(ArticleFilter articleFilter) {\n    70→    final var articlesEntity =\n    71→        find(\n    72→                \"select articles from ArticleEntity as articles inner join articles.author as author inner join author.followedBy as followedBy where followedBy.user.id = :loggedUserId\",\n    73→                Sort.descending(\"createdAt\").and(\"updatedAt\").descending(),\n    74→                Parameters.with(\"loggedUserId\", articleFilter.getLoggedUserId()))\n    75→            .page(Page.of(articleFilter.getOffset(), articleFilter.getLimit()))\n    76→            .list();\n    77→    final var articlesResult =\n    78→        articlesEntity.stream().map(entityUtils::article).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    79→    final var total = count(articleFilter.getLoggedUserId());\n    80→    return new PageResult<>(articlesResult, total);\n    81→  }\n    82→\n    83→  @Override\n    84→  public PageResult<Article> findArticlesByFilter(ArticleFilter filter) {\n    85→    Map<String, Object> params = new LinkedHashMap<>();\n    86→    SimpleQueryBuilder findArticlesQueryBuilder = new SimpleQueryBuilder();\n    87→    findArticlesQueryBuilder.addQueryStatement(\"select articles from ArticleEntity as articles\");\n    88→    configFilterFindArticlesQueryBuilder(\n    89→        findArticlesQueryBuilder,\n    90→        filter.getTags(),\n    91→        filter.getAuthors(),\n    92→        filter.getFavorited(),\n    93→        params);\n    94→    final var articlesEntity =\n    95→        find(\n    96→                findArticlesQueryBuilder.toQueryString(),\n    97→                Sort.descending(\"createdAt\").and(\"updatedAt\").descending(),\n    98→                params)\n    99→            .page(Page.of(filter.getOffset(), filter.getLimit()))\n   100→            .list();\n   101→    final var articlesResult =\n   102→        articlesEntity.stream().map(entityUtils::article).collect(Collectors.toList());\n   103→    final var total = count(filter.getTags(), filter.getAuthors(), filter.getFavorited());\n   104→    return new PageResult<>(articlesResult, total);\n   105→  }\n   106→\n   107→  @Override\n   108→  public long count(List<String> tags, List<String> authors, List<String> favorited) {\n   109→    Map<String, Object> params = new LinkedHashMap<>();\n   110→    SimpleQueryBuilder countArticlesQueryBuilder = new SimpleQueryBuilder();\n   111→    countArticlesQueryBuilder.addQueryStatement(\"from ArticleEntity as articles\");\n   112→    configFilterFindArticlesQueryBuilder(\n   113→        countArticlesQueryBuilder, tags, authors, favorited, params);\n   114→    return count(countArticlesQueryBuilder.toQueryString(), params);\n   115→  }\n   116→\n   117→  public long count(UUID loggedUserId) {\n   118→    return count(\n   119→        \"from ArticleEntity as articles inner join articles.author as author inner join author.followedBy as followedBy where followedBy.user.id = :loggedUserId\",\n   120→        Parameters.with(\"loggedUserId\", loggedUserId));\n   121→  }\n   122→\n   123→  private void configFilterFindArticlesQueryBuilder(\n   124→      SimpleQueryBuilder findArticlesQueryBuilder,\n   125→      List<String> tags,\n   126→      List<String> authors,\n   127→      List<String> favorited,\n   128→      Map<String, Object> params) {\n   129→\n   130→    findArticlesQueryBuilder.updateQueryStatementConditional(\n   131→        isNotEmpty(tags),\n   132→        \"inner join articles.tags as tags inner join tags.primaryKey.tag as tag\",\n   133→        \"upper(tag.name) in (:tags)\",\n   134→        () -> params.put(\"tags\", toUpperCase(tags)));\n   135→\n   136→    findArticlesQueryBuilder.updateQueryStatementConditional(\n   137→        isNotEmpty(authors),\n   138→        \"inner join articles.author as authors\",\n   139→        \"upper(authors.username) in (:authors)\",\n   140→        () -> params.put(\"authors\", toUpperCase(authors)));\n   141→\n   142→    findArticlesQueryBuilder.updateQueryStatementConditional(\n   143→        isNotEmpty(favorited),\n   144→        \"inner join articles.favorites as favorites inner join favorites.primaryKey.user as user\",\n   145→        \"upper(user.username) in (:favorites)\",\n   146→        () -> params.put(\"favorites\", toUpperCase(favorited)));\n   147→  }\n   148→}\n   149→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QWH2HE8revLKZ7i4nuJjFP","session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"4bbbfa10-26d8-4625-9a82-39ccdb1297b7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QwrxHL4mPSq7Q649VXQ2Fh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n     2→\n     3→import static io.quarkus.panache.common.Parameters.with;\n     4→\n     5→import io.quarkus.panache.common.Parameters;\n     6→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     7→import java.util.List;\n     8→import java.util.Optional;\n     9→import java.util.UUID;\n    10→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n    11→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n    15→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.CommentEntity;\n    16→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.EntityUtils;\n    17→\n    18→@ApplicationScoped\n    19→@AllArgsConstructor\n    20→public class CommentRepositoryPanache extends AbstractPanacheRepository<CommentEntity, UUID>\n    21→    implements CommentRepository {\n    22→\n    23→  private final EntityUtils entityUtils;\n    24→\n    25→  @Override\n    26→  public void save(Comment comment) {\n    27→    final var authorEntity = findUserEntityById(comment.getAuthor().getId());\n    28→    final var articleEntity = findArticleEntityById(comment.getArticle().getId());\n    29→    persist(new CommentEntity(authorEntity, articleEntity, comment));\n    30→  }\n    31→\n    32→  @Override\n    33→  public Optional<Comment> findByIdAndAuthor(UUID commentId, UUID authorId) {\n    34→    return find(\n    35→            \"id = :commentId and author.id = :authorId\",\n    36→            with(\"commentId\", commentId).and(\"authorId\", authorId))\n    37→        .firstResultOptional()\n    38→        .map(entityUtils::comment);\n    39→  }\n    40→\n    41→  @Override\n    42→  public void delete(Comment comment) {\n    43→    final var commentEntity = findCommentEntityById(comment.getId());\n    44→    delete(commentEntity);\n    45→  }\n    46→\n    47→  @Override\n    48→  public List<Comment> findCommentsByArticle(Article article) {\n    49→    final var commentsEntity =\n    50→        find(\"article.id = :articleId\", Parameters.with(\"articleId\", article.getId())).list();\n    51→    return commentsEntity.stream().map(entityUtils::comment).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    52→  }\n    53→}\n    54→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QWH2HE8revLKZ7i4nuJjFP","session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"88f4485d-c2e7-4878-b8f1-daff5d086745"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Wn2Ve375XbnqCkstjJfiUX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.panache.common.Parameters;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import java.util.Optional;\n     7→import java.util.UUID;\n     8→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     9→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagRepository;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.EntityUtils;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.TagEntity;\n    14→\n    15→@ApplicationScoped\n    16→@AllArgsConstructor\n    17→public class TagRepositoryPanache extends AbstractPanacheRepository<TagEntity, UUID>\n    18→    implements TagRepository {\n    19→\n    20→  private final EntityUtils entityUtils;\n    21→\n    22→  @Override\n    23→  public List<Tag> findAllTags() {\n    24→    return listAll().stream().map(entityUtils::tag).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    25→  }\n    26→\n    27→  @Override\n    28→  public Optional<Tag> findByName(String name) {\n    29→    return find(\"upper(name)\", name.toUpperCase().trim())\n    30→        .firstResultOptional()\n    31→        .map(entityUtils::tag);\n    32→  }\n    33→\n    34→  @Override\n    35→  public void save(Tag tag) {\n    36→    persist(new TagEntity(tag));\n    37→  }\n    38→\n    39→  @Override\n    40→  public List<Tag> findByNames(List<String> names) {\n    41→    final var tagsEntity =\n    42→        find(\n    43→                \"select tags from TagEntity as tags where upper(tags.name) in (:names)\",\n    44→                Parameters.with(\"names\", toUpperCase(names)))\n    45→            .list();\n    46→    return tagsEntity.stream().map(entityUtils::tag).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    47→  }\n    48→}\n    49→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QWH2HE8revLKZ7i4nuJjFP","session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"bff0682b-2f07-4665-9800-eb29766da8aa"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BqFKY2adH2VYMtv2CiYSGY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.panache.common.Parameters;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     7→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.TagRelationship;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.TagRelationshipRepository;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.EntityUtils;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.TagRelationshipEntity;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.TagRelationshipEntityKey;\n    15→\n    16→@ApplicationScoped\n    17→@AllArgsConstructor\n    18→public class TagRelationshipRepositoryPanache\n    19→    extends AbstractPanacheRepository<TagRelationshipEntity, TagRelationshipEntityKey>\n    20→    implements TagRelationshipRepository {\n    21→\n    22→  private final EntityUtils entityUtils;\n    23→\n    24→  @Override\n    25→  public void save(TagRelationship tagRelationship) {\n    26→    final var articleEntity = findArticleEntityById(tagRelationship.getArticle().getId());\n    27→    final var tagEntity = findTagEntityById(tagRelationship.getTag().getId());\n    28→    persist(new TagRelationshipEntity(articleEntity, tagEntity));\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  @Override\n    32→  public List<Tag> findArticleTags(Article article) {\n    33→    return find(\n    34→            \"from TagRelationshipEntity as tagRelationship where tagRelationship.primaryKey.article.id = :articleId\",\n    35→            Parameters.with(\"articleId\", article.getId()))\n    36→        .list()\n    37→        .stream()\n    38→        .map(entityUtils::tag)\n    39→        .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    40→  }\n    41→}\n    42→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QWH2HE8revLKZ7i4nuJjFP","session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"9d0c5c31-f257-41bb-9bf6-1c64964c2728"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012neKKKzRTjY8LHHVJcf9YW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n     2→\n     3→import static io.quarkus.panache.common.Parameters.with;\n     4→\n     5→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import java.util.Optional;\n     7→import java.util.UUID;\n     8→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.EntityUtils;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.FavoriteRelationshipEntity;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.FavoriteRelationshipEntityKey;\n    15→\n    16→@ApplicationScoped\n    17→@AllArgsConstructor\n    18→public class FavoriteRelationshipRepositoryPanache\n    19→    extends AbstractPanacheRepository<FavoriteRelationshipEntity, FavoriteRelationshipEntityKey>\n    20→    implements FavoriteRelationshipRepository {\n    21→\n    22→  private final EntityUtils entityUtils;\n    23→\n    24→  @Override\n    25→  public boolean isFavorited(Article article, UUID currentUserId) {\n    26→    return count(\n    27→            \"article.id = :articleId and user.id = :currentUserId\",\n    28→            with(\"articleId\", article.getId()).and(\"currentUserId\", currentUserId))\n    29→        > 0;\n    30→  }\n    31→\n    32→  @Override\n    33→  public long favoritesCount(Article article) {\n    34→    return count(\"article.id\", article.getId());\n    35→  }\n    36→\n    37→  @Override\n    38→  public Optional<FavoriteRelationship> findByArticleIdAndUserId(\n    39→      UUID articleId, UUID currentUserId) {\n    40→    return find(\n    41→            \"article.id = :articleId and user.id = :currentUserId\",\n    42→            with(\"articleId\", articleId).and(\"currentUserId\", currentUserId))\n    43→        .firstResultOptional()\n    44→        .map(entityUtils::favoriteRelationship);\n    45→  }\n    46→\n    47→  @Override\n    48→  public void save(FavoriteRelationship favoriteRelationship) {\n    49→    final var userEntity = findUserEntityById(favoriteRelationship.getUser().getId());\n    50→    final var articleEntity = findArticleEntityById(favoriteRelationship.getArticle().getId());\n    51→    persist(new FavoriteRelationshipEntity(userEntity, articleEntity));\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  @Override\n    55→  public void delete(FavoriteRelationship favoriteRelationship) {\n    56→    final var favoriteRelationshipEntity =\n    57→        findFavoriteRelationshipEntityByKey(favoriteRelationship);\n    58→    delete(favoriteRelationshipEntity);\n    59→  }\n    60→}\n    61→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QWH2HE8revLKZ7i4nuJjFP","session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"3eb7b11a-4941-41a7-b8a6-7de41d295560"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013v81BUwubioXtG1x3JyvUY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.panache.common.Parameters;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import java.util.Optional;\n     6→import java.util.UUID;\n     7→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationship;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationshipRepository;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.EntityUtils;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.FollowRelationshipEntity;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.FollowRelationshipEntityKey;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.UserEntity;\n    15→\n    16→@ApplicationScoped\n    17→@AllArgsConstructor\n    18→public class FollowRelationshipRepositoryPanache\n    19→    extends AbstractPanacheRepository<FollowRelationshipEntity, FollowRelationshipEntityKey>\n    20→    implements FollowRelationshipRepository {\n    21→\n    22→  private final EntityUtils entityUtils;\n    23→\n    24→  @Override\n    25→  public boolean isFollowing(UUID currentUserId, UUID followedUserId) {\n    26→    return count(\n    27→            \"primaryKey.user.id = :currentUserId and primaryKey.followed.id = :followedUserId\",\n    28→            Parameters.with(\"currentUserId\", currentUserId).and(\"followedUserId\", followedUserId))\n    29→        > 0;\n    30→  }\n    31→\n    32→  @Override\n    33→  public void save(FollowRelationship followRelationship) {\n    34→    final var userEntity = findUserEntityById(followRelationship.getUser().getId());\n    35→    final var userToFollowEntity = findUserEntityById(followRelationship.getFollowed().getId());\n    36→    persistAndFlush(new FollowRelationshipEntity(userEntity, userToFollowEntity));\n    37→  }\n    38→\n    39→  @Override\n    40→  public Optional<FollowRelationship> findByUsers(User loggedUser, User followedUser) {\n    41→    return findUsersFollowedEntityByUsers(loggedUser, followedUser)\n    42→        .map(this::followingRelationship);\n    43→  }\n    44→\n    45→  @Override\n    46→  public void remove(FollowRelationship followRelationship) {\n    47→    final var usersFollowedEntity =\n    48→        findUsersFollowedEntityByUsers(\n    49→                followRelationship.getUser(), followRelationship.getFollowed())\n    50→            .orElseThrow();\n    51→    delete(usersFollowedEntity);\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  private Optional<FollowRelationshipEntity> findUsersFollowedEntityByUsers(\n    55→      User loggedUser, User followedUser) {\n    56→    final var loggedUserEntity = findUserEntityById(loggedUser.getId());\n    57→    final var followedEntity = findUserEntityById(followedUser.getId());\n    58→    return find(\"primaryKey\", usersFollowedKey(loggedUserEntity, followedEntity))\n    59→        .firstResultOptional();\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  private FollowRelationship followingRelationship(\n    63→      FollowRelationshipEntity followRelationshipEntity) {\n    64→    final var user = entityUtils.user(followRelationshipEntity.getUser());\n    65→    final var followed = entityUtils.user(followRelationshipEntity.getFollowed());\n    66→    return new FollowRelationship(user, followed);\n    67→  }\n    68→\n    69→  private FollowRelationshipEntityKey usersFollowedKey(UserEntity user, UserEntity followed) {\n    70→    final var primaryKey = new FollowRelationshipEntityKey();\n    71→    primaryKey.setUser(user);\n    72→    primaryKey.setFollowed(followed);\n    73→    return primaryKey;\n    74→  }\n    75→}\n    76→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QWH2HE8revLKZ7i4nuJjFP","session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"b582244e-bcda-4d24-9601-f135adc7f6ef"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VHxp5jLfkcZCzDL8na5h9T","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.annotation.security.RolesAllowed;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.Valid;\n     7→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.*;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Context;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\n    13→import java.util.UUID;\n    14→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n    15→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.UpdateUserRequest;\n    16→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.UserResponse;\n    17→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\n    18→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UpdateUser;\n    19→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n    20→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider.JwtTokenProvider;\n    21→\n    22→@Path(\"/user\")\n    23→@AllArgsConstructor\n    24→public class UserResource {\n    25→\n    26→  private final FindUserById findUserById;\n    27→  private final UpdateUser updateUser;\n    28→  @Inject JwtTokenProvider tokenProvider;\n    29→\n    30→  @GET\n    31→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n    32→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    33→  public Response getUser(@Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n    34→    final var userId = UUID.fromString(securityContext.getUserPrincipal().getName());\n    35→    final var user = findUserById.handle(userId);\n    36→    final var token = tokenProvider.createUserToken(user.getId().toString());\n    37→    return Response.ok(new UserResponse(user, token)).status(Response.Status.OK).build();\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  @PUT\n    41→  @Transactional\n    42→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n    43→  @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    44→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    45→  public Response update(\n    46→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext,\n    47→      @Valid @NotNull(message = ValidationMessages.REQUEST_BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_NULL)\n    48→          UpdateUserRequest updateUserRequest) {\n    49→    final var userId = UUID.fromString(securityContext.getUserPrincipal().getName());\n    50→    final var user = updateUser.handle(updateUserRequest.toUpdateUserInput(userId));\n    51→    final var token = tokenProvider.createUserToken(user.getId().toString());\n    52→    return Response.ok(new UserResponse(user, token)).status(Response.Status.OK).build();\n    53→  }\n    54→}\n    55→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QWH2HE8revLKZ7i4nuJjFP","session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"7f30d311-9026-477c-bb08-679e96ac750f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016J7gaYucwJhv6WTXQbSvup","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.annotation.security.PermitAll;\n     4→import jakarta.annotation.security.RolesAllowed;\n     5→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.*;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Context;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\n    12→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.utils.ResourceUtils;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FollowUserByUsername;\n    15→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UnfollowUserByUsername;\n    16→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n    17→\n    18→@Path(\"/profiles\")\n    19→@AllArgsConstructor\n    20→public class ProfilesResource {\n    21→\n    22→  private final FollowUserByUsername followUserByUsername;\n    23→  private final UnfollowUserByUsername unfollowUserByUsername;\n    24→  private final ResourceUtils resourceUtils;\n    25→\n    26→  @GET\n    27→  @PermitAll\n    28→  @Path(\"/{username}\")\n    29→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    30→  public Response getProfile(\n    31→      @PathParam(\"username\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.USERNAME_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    32→          String username,\n    33→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n    34→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n    35→    final var profileResponse = resourceUtils.profileResponse(username, loggedUserId);\n    36→    return Response.ok(profileResponse).status(Response.Status.OK).build();\n    37→  }\n    38→\n    39→  @POST\n    40→  @Transactional\n    41→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n    42→  @Path(\"/{username}/follow\")\n    43→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    44→  public Response follow(\n    45→      @PathParam(\"username\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.USERNAME_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    46→          String username,\n    47→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n    48→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n    49→    followUserByUsername.handle(loggedUserId, username);\n    50→    return Response.ok(resourceUtils.profileResponse(username, loggedUserId))\n    51→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n    52→        .build();\n    53→  }\n    54→\n    55→  @DELETE\n    56→  @Transactional\n    57→  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n    58→  @Path(\"/{username}/follow\")\n    59→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    60→  public Response unfollow(\n    61→      @PathParam(\"username\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.USERNAME_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n    62→          String username,\n    63→      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n    64→    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n    65→    unfollowUserByUsername.handle(loggedUserId, username);\n    66→    return Response.ok(resourceUtils.profileResponse(username, loggedUserId))\n    67→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n    68→        .build();\n    69→  }\n    70→}\n    71→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QWH2HE8revLKZ7i4nuJjFP","session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"3ed3b47d-38c2-4000-968b-a4779e42fb13"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RsnCbuMD6cwRscSPQd5itZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n     6→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    10→import java.util.List;\n    11→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.TagsResponse;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindTags;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n    15→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers.NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper;\n    16→\n    17→@Path(\"/tags\")\n    18→@AllArgsConstructor\n    19→public class TagsResource {\n    20→\n    21→  @NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n    22→  private final FindTags findTags;\n    23→\n    24→  @GET\n    25→  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    26→  public Response getTags() throws JsonProcessingException {\n    27→    List<Tag> tags = findTags.handle();\n    28→    return Response.ok(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new TagsResponse(tags)))\n    29→        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n    30→        .build();\n    31→  }\n    32→}\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QWH2HE8revLKZ7i4nuJjFP","session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"e5f8cf58-5850-41a2-8ea7-645ae35953a7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Xiw8btARzPmunqKHKjmqb2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.utils;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\n     5→import java.security.Principal;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import java.util.UUID;\n     8→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     9→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.*;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.*;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.PageResult;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n    15→\n    16→@ApplicationScoped\n    17→@AllArgsConstructor\n    18→public class ResourceUtils {\n    19→\n    20→  private static final int DEFAULT_LIMIT = 20;\n    21→  private final FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername;\n    22→  private final IsFollowingUser isFollowingUser;\n    23→  private final FindArticleTags findArticleTags;\n    24→  private final IsArticleFavorited isArticleFavorited;\n    25→  private final ArticleFavoritesCount articleFavoritesCount;\n    26→\n    27→  public ProfileResponse profileResponse(String username, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    28→    final var user = findUserByUsername.handle(username);\n    29→    final var profileResponse = new ProfileResponse(user);\n    30→    if (loggedUserId != null) {\n    31→      profileResponse.setFollowing(isFollowingUser.handle(loggedUserId, user.getId()));\n    32→    }\n    33→    return profileResponse;\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  public ArticleResponse articleResponse(Article article, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    37→    final var author = article.getAuthor();\n    38→    final var profileResponse = profileResponse(author.getUsername(), author.getId());\n    39→    final var tags = findArticleTags.handle(article);\n    40→    final var favoritesCount = articleFavoritesCount.handle(article.getId());\n    41→    final var articleResponse = new ArticleResponse(article, profileResponse, favoritesCount, tags);\n    42→    if (loggedUserId != null) {\n    43→      articleResponse.setFavorited(isArticleFavorited.handle(article, loggedUserId));\n    44→    }\n    45→    return articleResponse;\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  public ArticlesResponse articlesResponse(PageResult<Article> pageResult, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    49→    final var resultResponse =\n    50→        pageResult.getResult().stream()\n    51→            .map(article -> articleResponse(article, loggedUserId))\n    52→            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    53→    return new ArticlesResponse(resultResponse, pageResult.getTotal());\n    54→  }\n    55→\n    56→  public CommentResponse commentResponse(Comment comment, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    57→    final var commentAuthor = comment.getAuthor();\n    58→    final var authorResponse = profileResponse(commentAuthor.getUsername(), loggedUserId);\n    59→    return new CommentResponse(comment, authorResponse);\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  public UUID getLoggedUserId(SecurityContext securityContext) {\n    63→    Principal principal = securityContext.getUserPrincipal();\n    64→    return principal != null ? UUID.fromString(principal.getName()) : null;\n    65→  }\n    66→\n    67→  public CommentsResponse commentsResponse(List<Comment> comments, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    68→    final var resultResponse =\n    69→        comments.stream()\n    70→            .map(comment -> commentResponse(comment, loggedUserId))\n    71→            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    72→    return new CommentsResponse(resultResponse);\n    73→  }\n    74→\n    75→  public int getLimit(int limit) {\n    76→    return limit > 0 ? limit : DEFAULT_LIMIT;\n    77→  }\n    78→}\n    79→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QWH2HE8revLKZ7i4nuJjFP","session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"1c2973c5-d192-426d-8562-393dd9435443"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QWH2HE8revLKZ7i4nuJjFP","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the complete contents of all 12 files:\n\n---\n\n## 1. AbstractPanacheRepository.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/AbstractPanacheRepository.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n\nimport io.quarkus.hibernate.orm.panache.PanacheRepositoryBase;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.UUID;\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.*;\n\npublic class AbstractPanacheRepository<ENTITY, ID> implements PanacheRepositoryBase<ENTITY, ID> {\n\n  protected UserEntity findUserEntityById(UUID id) {\n    return getEntityManager().find(UserEntity.class, id);\n  }\n\n  protected TagEntity findTagEntityById(UUID id) {\n    return getEntityManager().find(TagEntity.class, id);\n  }\n\n  protected ArticleEntity findArticleEntityById(UUID id) {\n    return getEntityManager().find(ArticleEntity.class, id);\n  }\n\n  protected CommentEntity findCommentEntityById(UUID id) {\n    return getEntityManager().find(CommentEntity.class, id);\n  }\n\n  protected FavoriteRelationshipEntity findFavoriteRelationshipEntityByKey(\n      FavoriteRelationship favoriteRelationship) {\n\n    final var userEntity = findUserEntityById(favoriteRelationship.getUser().getId());\n    final var articleEntity = findArticleEntityById(favoriteRelationship.getArticle().getId());\n\n    final var favoriteRelationshipEntityKey = new FavoriteRelationshipEntityKey();\n    favoriteRelationshipEntityKey.setUser(userEntity);\n    favoriteRelationshipEntityKey.setArticle(articleEntity);\n\n    return getEntityManager().find(FavoriteRelationshipEntity.class, favoriteRelationshipEntityKey);\n  }\n\n  protected boolean isNotEmpty(List<?> list) {\n    return list != null && !list.isEmpty();\n  }\n\n  protected List<String> toUpperCase(List<String> subjectList) {\n    return subjectList.stream().map(String::toUpperCase).collect(Collectors.toList());\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. UserRepositoryPanache.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/UserRepositoryPanache.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n\nimport static io.quarkus.panache.common.Parameters.with;\n\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport java.util.Optional;\nimport java.util.UUID;\nimport lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserRepository;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.EntityUtils;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.UserEntity;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@AllArgsConstructor\npublic class UserRepositoryPanache extends AbstractPanacheRepository<UserEntity, UUID>\n    implements UserRepository {\n\n  private final EntityUtils entityUtils;\n\n  @Override\n  public void save(User user) {\n    persist(new UserEntity(user));\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public boolean existsBy(String field, String value) {\n    return count(\"upper(\" + field + \")\", value.toUpperCase().trim()) > 0;\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public Optional<User> findByEmail(String email) {\n    return find(\"upper(email)\", email.toUpperCase().trim())\n        .firstResultOptional()\n        .map(entityUtils::user);\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public Optional<User> findUserById(UUID id) {\n    return findByIdOptional(id).map(entityUtils::user);\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public boolean existsUsername(UUID excludeId, String username) {\n    return count(\n            \"id != :excludeId and upper(username) = :username\",\n            with(\"excludeId\", excludeId).and(\"username\", username.toUpperCase().trim()))\n        > 0;\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public boolean existsEmail(UUID excludeId, String email) {\n    return count(\n            \"id != :excludeId and upper(email) = :email\",\n            with(\"excludeId\", excludeId).and(\"email\", email.toUpperCase().trim()))\n        > 0;\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public void update(User user) {\n    final var userEntity = findById(user.getId());\n    userEntity.update(user);\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public Optional<User> findByUsername(String username) {\n    return find(\"upper(username)\", username.toUpperCase().trim())\n        .firstResultOptional()\n        .map(entityUtils::user);\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. ArticleRepositoryPanache.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/ArticleRepositoryPanache.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n\nimport io.quarkus.panache.common.Page;\nimport io.quarkus.panache.common.Parameters;\nimport io.quarkus.panache.common.Sort;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport java.util.*;\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\nimport lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleFilter;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.PageResult;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.ArticleEntity;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.EntityUtils;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache.utils.SimpleQueryBuilder;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@AllArgsConstructor\npublic class ArticleRepositoryPanache extends AbstractPanacheRepository<ArticleEntity, UUID>\n    implements ArticleRepository {\n\n  private final EntityUtils entityUtils;\n\n  @Override\n  public boolean existsBySlug(String slug) {\n    return count(\"upper(slug)\", slug.toUpperCase().trim()) > 0;\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public void save(Article article) {\n    final var author = findUserEntityById(article.getAuthor().getId());\n    persistAndFlush(new ArticleEntity(article, author));\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public Optional<Article> findArticleById(UUID id) {\n    return findByIdOptional(id).map(entityUtils::article);\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public Optional<Article> findBySlug(String slug) {\n    return find(\"upper(slug)\", slug.toUpperCase().trim())\n        .firstResultOptional()\n        .map(entityUtils::article);\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public void update(Article article) {\n    final var articleEntity = findArticleEntityById(article.getId());\n    articleEntity.update(article);\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public Optional<Article> findByAuthorAndSlug(UUID authorId, String slug) {\n    return find(\n            \"author.id = :authorId and upper(slug) = :slug\",\n            Parameters.with(\"authorId\", authorId).and(\"slug\", slug.toUpperCase().trim()))\n        .firstResultOptional()\n        .map(entityUtils::article);\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public void delete(Article article) {\n    deleteById(article.getId());\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public PageResult<Article> findMostRecentArticlesByFilter(ArticleFilter articleFilter) {\n    final var articlesEntity =\n        find(\n                \"select articles from ArticleEntity as articles inner join articles.author as author inner join author.followedBy as followedBy where followedBy.user.id = :loggedUserId\",\n                Sort.descending(\"createdAt\").and(\"updatedAt\").descending(),\n                Parameters.with(\"loggedUserId\", articleFilter.getLoggedUserId()))\n            .page(Page.of(articleFilter.getOffset(), articleFilter.getLimit()))\n            .list();\n    final var articlesResult =\n        articlesEntity.stream().map(entityUtils::article).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    final var total = count(articleFilter.getLoggedUserId());\n    return new PageResult<>(articlesResult, total);\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public PageResult<Article> findArticlesByFilter(ArticleFilter filter) {\n    Map<String, Object> params = new LinkedHashMap<>();\n    SimpleQueryBuilder findArticlesQueryBuilder = new SimpleQueryBuilder();\n    findArticlesQueryBuilder.addQueryStatement(\"select articles from ArticleEntity as articles\");\n    configFilterFindArticlesQueryBuilder(\n        findArticlesQueryBuilder,\n        filter.getTags(),\n        filter.getAuthors(),\n        filter.getFavorited(),\n        params);\n    final var articlesEntity =\n        find(\n                findArticlesQueryBuilder.toQueryString(),\n                Sort.descending(\"createdAt\").and(\"updatedAt\").descending(),\n                params)\n            .page(Page.of(filter.getOffset(), filter.getLimit()))\n            .list();\n    final var articlesResult =\n        articlesEntity.stream().map(entityUtils::article).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    final var total = count(filter.getTags(), filter.getAuthors(), filter.getFavorited());\n    return new PageResult<>(articlesResult, total);\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public long count(List<String> tags, List<String> authors, List<String> favorited) {\n    Map<String, Object> params = new LinkedHashMap<>();\n    SimpleQueryBuilder countArticlesQueryBuilder = new SimpleQueryBuilder();\n    countArticlesQueryBuilder.addQueryStatement(\"from ArticleEntity as articles\");\n    configFilterFindArticlesQueryBuilder(\n        countArticlesQueryBuilder, tags, authors, favorited, params);\n    return count(countArticlesQueryBuilder.toQueryString(), params);\n  }\n\n  public long count(UUID loggedUserId) {\n    return count(\n        \"from ArticleEntity as articles inner join articles.author as author inner join author.followedBy as followedBy where followedBy.user.id = :loggedUserId\",\n        Parameters.with(\"loggedUserId\", loggedUserId));\n  }\n\n  private void configFilterFindArticlesQueryBuilder(\n      SimpleQueryBuilder findArticlesQueryBuilder,\n      List<String> tags,\n      List<String> authors,\n      List<String> favorited,\n      Map<String, Object> params) {\n\n    findArticlesQueryBuilder.updateQueryStatementConditional(\n        isNotEmpty(tags),\n        \"inner join articles.tags as tags inner join tags.primaryKey.tag as tag\",\n        \"upper(tag.name) in (:tags)\",\n        () -> params.put(\"tags\", toUpperCase(tags)));\n\n    findArticlesQueryBuilder.updateQueryStatementConditional(\n        isNotEmpty(authors),\n        \"inner join articles.author as authors\",\n        \"upper(authors.username) in (:authors)\",\n        () -> params.put(\"authors\", toUpperCase(authors)));\n\n    findArticlesQueryBuilder.updateQueryStatementConditional(\n        isNotEmpty(favorited),\n        \"inner join articles.favorites as favorites inner join favorites.primaryKey.user as user\",\n        \"upper(user.username) in (:favorites)\",\n        () -> params.put(\"favorites\", toUpperCase(favorited)));\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. CommentRepositoryPanache.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/CommentRepositoryPanache.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n\nimport static io.quarkus.panache.common.Parameters.with;\n\nimport io.quarkus.panache.common.Parameters;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Optional;\nimport java.util.UUID;\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\nimport lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.CommentEntity;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.EntityUtils;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@AllArgsConstructor\npublic class CommentRepositoryPanache extends AbstractPanacheRepository<CommentEntity, UUID>\n    implements CommentRepository {\n\n  private final EntityUtils entityUtils;\n\n  @Override\n  public void save(Comment comment) {\n    final var authorEntity = findUserEntityById(comment.getAuthor().getId());\n    final var articleEntity = findArticleEntityById(comment.getArticle().getId());\n    persist(new CommentEntity(authorEntity, articleEntity, comment));\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public Optional<Comment> findByIdAndAuthor(UUID commentId, UUID authorId) {\n    return find(\n            \"id = :commentId and author.id = :authorId\",\n            with(\"commentId\", commentId).and(\"authorId\", authorId))\n        .firstResultOptional()\n        .map(entityUtils::comment);\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public void delete(Comment comment) {\n    final var commentEntity = findCommentEntityById(comment.getId());\n    delete(commentEntity);\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public List<Comment> findCommentsByArticle(Article article) {\n    final var commentsEntity =\n        find(\"article.id = :articleId\", Parameters.with(\"articleId\", article.getId())).list();\n    return commentsEntity.stream().map(entityUtils::comment).collect(Collectors.toList());\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. TagRepositoryPanache.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/TagRepositoryPanache.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n\nimport io.quarkus.panache.common.Parameters;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Optional;\nimport java.util.UUID;\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\nimport lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagRepository;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.EntityUtils;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.TagEntity;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@AllArgsConstructor\npublic class TagRepositoryPanache extends AbstractPanacheRepository<TagEntity, UUID>\n    implements TagRepository {\n\n  private final EntityUtils entityUtils;\n\n  @Override\n  public List<Tag> findAllTags() {\n    return listAll().stream().map(entityUtils::tag).collect(Collectors.toList());\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public Optional<Tag> findByName(String name) {\n    return find(\"upper(name)\", name.toUpperCase().trim())\n        .firstResultOptional()\n        .map(entityUtils::tag);\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public void save(Tag tag) {\n    persist(new TagEntity(tag));\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public List<Tag> findByNames(List<String> names) {\n    final var tagsEntity =\n        find(\n                \"select tags from TagEntity as tags where upper(tags.name) in (:names)\",\n                Parameters.with(\"names\", toUpperCase(names)))\n            .list();\n    return tagsEntity.stream().map(entityUtils::tag).collect(Collectors.toList());\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. TagRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/TagRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n\nimport io.quarkus.panache.common.Parameters;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\nimport lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.TagRelationship;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.TagRelationshipRepository;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.EntityUtils;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.TagRelationshipEntity;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.TagRelationshipEntityKey;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@AllArgsConstructor\npublic class TagRelationshipRepositoryPanache\n    extends AbstractPanacheRepository<TagRelationshipEntity, TagRelationshipEntityKey>\n    implements TagRelationshipRepository {\n\n  private final EntityUtils entityUtils;\n\n  @Override\n  public void save(TagRelationship tagRelationship) {\n    final var articleEntity = findArticleEntityById(tagRelationship.getArticle().getId());\n    final var tagEntity = findTagEntityById(tagRelationship.getTag().getId());\n    persist(new TagRelationshipEntity(articleEntity, tagEntity));\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public List<Tag> findArticleTags(Article article) {\n    return find(\n            \"from TagRelationshipEntity as tagRelationship where tagRelationship.primaryKey.article.id = :articleId\",\n            Parameters.with(\"articleId\", article.getId()))\n        .list()\n        .stream()\n        .map(entityUtils::tag)\n        .collect(Collectors.toList());\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. FavoriteRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/FavoriteRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n\nimport static io.quarkus.panache.common.Parameters.with;\n\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport java.util.Optional;\nimport java.util.UUID;\nimport lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.EntityUtils;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.FavoriteRelationshipEntity;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.FavoriteRelationshipEntityKey;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@AllArgsConstructor\npublic class FavoriteRelationshipRepositoryPanache\n    extends AbstractPanacheRepository<FavoriteRelationshipEntity, FavoriteRelationshipEntityKey>\n    implements FavoriteRelationshipRepository {\n\n  private final EntityUtils entityUtils;\n\n  @Override\n  public boolean isFavorited(Article article, UUID currentUserId) {\n    return count(\n            \"article.id = :articleId and user.id = :currentUserId\",\n            with(\"articleId\", article.getId()).and(\"currentUserId\", currentUserId))\n        > 0;\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public long favoritesCount(Article article) {\n    return count(\"article.id\", article.getId());\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public Optional<FavoriteRelationship> findByArticleIdAndUserId(\n      UUID articleId, UUID currentUserId) {\n    return find(\n            \"article.id = :articleId and user.id = :currentUserId\",\n            with(\"articleId\", articleId).and(\"currentUserId\", currentUserId))\n        .firstResultOptional()\n        .map(entityUtils::favoriteRelationship);\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public void save(FavoriteRelationship favoriteRelationship) {\n    final var userEntity = findUserEntityById(favoriteRelationship.getUser().getId());\n    final var articleEntity = findArticleEntityById(favoriteRelationship.getArticle().getId());\n    persist(new FavoriteRelationshipEntity(userEntity, articleEntity));\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public void delete(FavoriteRelationship favoriteRelationship) {\n    final var favoriteRelationshipEntity =\n        findFavoriteRelationshipEntityByKey(favoriteRelationship);\n    delete(favoriteRelationshipEntity);\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. FollowRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/repository/hibernate/panache/FollowRelationshipRepositoryPanache.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.panache;\n\nimport io.quarkus.panache.common.Parameters;\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport java.util.Optional;\nimport java.util.UUID;\nimport lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationship;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationshipRepository;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.EntityUtils;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.FollowRelationshipEntity;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.FollowRelationshipEntityKey;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity.UserEntity;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@AllArgsConstructor\npublic class FollowRelationshipRepositoryPanache\n    extends AbstractPanacheRepository<FollowRelationshipEntity, FollowRelationshipEntityKey>\n    implements FollowRelationshipRepository {\n\n  private final EntityUtils entityUtils;\n\n  @Override\n  public boolean isFollowing(UUID currentUserId, UUID followedUserId) {\n    return count(\n            \"primaryKey.user.id = :currentUserId and primaryKey.followed.id = :followedUserId\",\n            Parameters.with(\"currentUserId\", currentUserId).and(\"followedUserId\", followedUserId))\n        > 0;\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public void save(FollowRelationship followRelationship) {\n    final var userEntity = findUserEntityById(followRelationship.getUser().getId());\n    final var userToFollowEntity = findUserEntityById(followRelationship.getFollowed().getId());\n    persistAndFlush(new FollowRelationshipEntity(userEntity, userToFollowEntity));\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public Optional<FollowRelationship> findByUsers(User loggedUser, User followedUser) {\n    return findUsersFollowedEntityByUsers(loggedUser, followedUser)\n        .map(this::followingRelationship);\n  }\n\n  @Override\n  public void remove(FollowRelationship followRelationship) {\n    final var usersFollowedEntity =\n        findUsersFollowedEntityByUsers(\n                followRelationship.getUser(), followRelationship.getFollowed())\n            .orElseThrow();\n    delete(usersFollowedEntity);\n  }\n\n  private Optional<FollowRelationshipEntity> findUsersFollowedEntityByUsers(\n      User loggedUser, User followedUser) {\n    final var loggedUserEntity = findUserEntityById(loggedUser.getId());\n    final var followedEntity = findUserEntityById(followedUser.getId());\n    return find(\"primaryKey\", usersFollowedKey(loggedUserEntity, followedEntity))\n        .firstResultOptional();\n  }\n\n  private FollowRelationship followingRelationship(\n      FollowRelationshipEntity followRelationshipEntity) {\n    final var user = entityUtils.user(followRelationshipEntity.getUser());\n    final var followed = entityUtils.user(followRelationshipEntity.getFollowed());\n    return new FollowRelationship(user, followed);\n  }\n\n  private FollowRelationshipEntityKey usersFollowedKey(UserEntity user, UserEntity followed) {\n    final var primaryKey = new FollowRelationshipEntityKey();\n    primaryKey.setUser(user);\n    primaryKey.setFollowed(followed);\n    return primaryKey;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 9. UserResource.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/UserResource.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n\nimport jakarta.annotation.security.RolesAllowed;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\nimport jakarta.validation.Valid;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.*;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Context;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\nimport java.util.UUID;\nimport lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.request.UpdateUserRequest;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.UserResponse;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindUserById;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UpdateUser;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider.JwtTokenProvider;\n\n@Path(\"/user\")\n@AllArgsConstructor\npublic class UserResource {\n\n  private final FindUserById findUserById;\n  private final UpdateUser updateUser;\n  @Inject JwtTokenProvider tokenProvider;\n\n  @GET\n  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n  public Response getUser(@Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n    final var userId = UUID.fromString(securityContext.getUserPrincipal().getName());\n    final var user = findUserById.handle(userId);\n    final var token = tokenProvider.createUserToken(user.getId().toString());\n    return Response.ok(new UserResponse(user, token)).status(Response.Status.OK).build();\n  }\n\n  @PUT\n  @Transactional\n  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n  @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n  public Response update(\n      @Context SecurityContext securityContext,\n      @Valid @NotNull(message = ValidationMessages.REQUEST_BODY_MUST_BE_NOT_NULL)\n          UpdateUserRequest updateUserRequest) {\n    final var userId = UUID.fromString(securityContext.getUserPrincipal().getName());\n    final var user = updateUser.handle(updateUserRequest.toUpdateUserInput(userId));\n    final var token = tokenProvider.createUserToken(user.getId().toString());\n    return Response.ok(new UserResponse(user, token)).status(Response.Status.OK).build();\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 10. ProfilesResource.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/ProfilesResource.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n\nimport jakarta.annotation.security.PermitAll;\nimport jakarta.annotation.security.RolesAllowed;\nimport jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\nimport jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.*;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Context;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\nimport lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.utils.ResourceUtils;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FollowUserByUsername;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UnfollowUserByUsername;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.constants.ValidationMessages;\n\n@Path(\"/profiles\")\n@AllArgsConstructor\npublic class ProfilesResource {\n\n  private final FollowUserByUsername followUserByUsername;\n  private final UnfollowUserByUsername unfollowUserByUsername;\n  private final ResourceUtils resourceUtils;\n\n  @GET\n  @PermitAll\n  @Path(\"/{username}\")\n  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n  public Response getProfile(\n      @PathParam(\"username\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.USERNAME_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n          String username,\n      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n    final var profileResponse = resourceUtils.profileResponse(username, loggedUserId);\n    return Response.ok(profileResponse).status(Response.Status.OK).build();\n  }\n\n  @POST\n  @Transactional\n  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n  @Path(\"/{username}/follow\")\n  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n  public Response follow(\n      @PathParam(\"username\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.USERNAME_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n          String username,\n      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n    followUserByUsername.handle(loggedUserId, username);\n    return Response.ok(resourceUtils.profileResponse(username, loggedUserId))\n        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n        .build();\n  }\n\n  @DELETE\n  @Transactional\n  @RolesAllowed({\"USER\", \"ADMIN\"})\n  @Path(\"/{username}/follow\")\n  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n  public Response unfollow(\n      @PathParam(\"username\") @NotBlank(message = ValidationMessages.USERNAME_MUST_BE_NOT_BLANK)\n          String username,\n      @Context SecurityContext securityContext) {\n    final var loggedUserId = resourceUtils.getLoggedUserId(securityContext);\n    unfollowUserByUsername.handle(loggedUserId, username);\n    return Response.ok(resourceUtils.profileResponse(username, loggedUserId))\n        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n        .build();\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 11. TagsResource.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/TagsResource.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.TagsResponse;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindTags;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers.NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper;\n\n@Path(\"/tags\")\n@AllArgsConstructor\npublic class TagsResource {\n\n  @NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n  private final FindTags findTags;\n\n  @GET\n  @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n  public Response getTags() throws JsonProcessingException {\n    List<Tag> tags = findTags.handle();\n    return Response.ok(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new TagsResponse(tags)))\n        .status(Response.Status.OK)\n        .build();\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 12. ResourceUtils.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/utils/ResourceUtils.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.utils;\n\nimport jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\nimport java.security.Principal;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.UUID;\nimport java.util.stream.Collectors;\nimport lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.*;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.*;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.PageResult;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n\n@ApplicationScoped\n@AllArgsConstructor\npublic class ResourceUtils {\n\n  private static final int DEFAULT_LIMIT = 20;\n  private final FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername;\n  private final IsFollowingUser isFollowingUser;\n  private final FindArticleTags findArticleTags;\n  private final IsArticleFavorited isArticleFavorited;\n  private final ArticleFavoritesCount articleFavoritesCount;\n\n  public ProfileResponse profileResponse(String username, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    final var user = findUserByUsername.handle(username);\n    final var profileResponse = new ProfileResponse(user);\n    if (loggedUserId != null) {\n      profileResponse.setFollowing(isFollowingUser.handle(loggedUserId, user.getId()));\n    }\n    return profileResponse;\n  }\n\n  public ArticleResponse articleResponse(Article article, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    final var author = article.getAuthor();\n    final var profileResponse = profileResponse(author.getUsername(), author.getId());\n    final var tags = findArticleTags.handle(article);\n    final var favoritesCount = articleFavoritesCount.handle(article.getId());\n    final var articleResponse = new ArticleResponse(article, profileResponse, favoritesCount, tags);\n    if (loggedUserId != null) {\n      articleResponse.setFavorited(isArticleFavorited.handle(article, loggedUserId));\n    }\n    return articleResponse;\n  }\n\n  public ArticlesResponse articlesResponse(PageResult<Article> pageResult, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    final var resultResponse =\n        pageResult.getResult().stream()\n            .map(article -> articleResponse(article, loggedUserId))\n            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    return new ArticlesResponse(resultResponse, pageResult.getTotal());\n  }\n\n  public CommentResponse commentResponse(Comment comment, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    final var commentAuthor = comment.getAuthor();\n    final var authorResponse = profileResponse(commentAuthor.getUsername(), loggedUserId);\n    return new CommentResponse(comment, authorResponse);\n  }\n\n  public UUID getLoggedUserId(SecurityContext securityContext) {\n    Principal principal = securityContext.getUserPrincipal();\n    return principal != null ? UUID.fromString(principal.getName()) : null;\n  }\n\n  public CommentsResponse commentsResponse(List<Comment> comments, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    final var resultResponse =\n        comments.stream()\n            .map(comment -> commentResponse(comment, loggedUserId))\n            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    return new CommentsResponse(resultResponse);\n  }\n\n  public int getLimit(int limit) {\n    return limit > 0 ? limit : DEFAULT_LIMIT;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\nAll files have been read and their complete contents are provided above. These files appear to be part of a Quarkus-based implementation of the RealWorld API specification, using Jakarta EE, Panache for data persistence, and following a clean architecture pattern with domain models, repositories, and web resources."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"14290778-8deb-4819-a1a3-6ebccc60b3e8"}
