{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TWJRvpcSWSantB42MQsdQm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n     2→<project xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 https://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\"\n     3→         xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\"\n     4→         xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\">\n     5→    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n     6→    <groupId>org.example</groupId>\n     7→    <artifactId>realworldapiservice</artifactId>\n     8→    <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>\n     9→    <properties>\n    10→        <compiler-plugin.version>3.14.0</compiler-plugin.version>\n    11→        <failsafe.useModulePath>false</failsafe.useModulePath>\n    12→        <maven.compiler.release>21</maven.compiler.release>\n    13→        <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n    14→        <project.reporting.outputEncoding>UTF-8</project.reporting.outputEncoding>\n    15→        <quarkus.platform.artifact-id>quarkus-bom</quarkus.platform.artifact-id>\n    16→        <quarkus.platform.group-id>io.quarkus.platform</quarkus.platform.group-id>\n    17→        <quarkus.platform.version>3.30.5</quarkus.platform.version>\n    18→        <surefire-plugin.version>3.5.3</surefire-plugin.version>\n    19→        <spotless.version>2.46.1</spotless.version>\n    20→    </properties>\n    21→    <dependencyManagement>\n    22→        <dependencies>\n    23→            <dependency>\n    24→                <groupId>${quarkus.platform.group-id}</groupId>\n    25→                <artifactId>${quarkus.platform.artifact-id}</artifactId>\n    26→                <version>${quarkus.platform.version}</version>\n    27→                <type>pom</type>\n    28→                <scope>import</scope>\n    29→            </dependency>\n    30→        </dependencies>\n    31→    </dependencyManagement>\n    32→    <dependencies>\n    33→        <dependency>\n    34→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    35→            <artifactId>quarkus-junit5</artifactId>\n    36→            <scope>test</scope>\n    37→        </dependency>\n    38→        <dependency>\n    39→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    40→            <artifactId>quarkus-smallrye-health</artifactId>\n    41→        </dependency>\n    42→        <dependency>\n    43→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    44→            <artifactId>quarkus-rest-jackson</artifactId>\n    45→        </dependency>\n    46→        <dependency>\n    47→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    48→            <artifactId>quarkus-jdbc-postgresql</artifactId>\n    49→        </dependency>\n    50→        <dependency>\n    51→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    52→            <artifactId>quarkus-jdbc-h2</artifactId>\n    53→        </dependency>\n    54→        <dependency>\n    55→            <groupId>io.rest-assured</groupId>\n    56→            <artifactId>rest-assured</artifactId>\n    57→            <scope>test</scope>\n    58→        </dependency>\n    59→        <dependency>\n    60→            <groupId>org.powermock</groupId>\n    61→            <artifactId>powermock-api-mockito2</artifactId>\n    62→            <version>2.0.9</version>\n    63→            <scope>test</scope>\n    64→        </dependency>\n    65→        <dependency>\n    66→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    67→            <artifactId>quarkus-elytron-security</artifactId>\n    68→        </dependency>\n    69→        <dependency>\n    70→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    71→            <artifactId>quarkus-hibernate-validator</artifactId>\n    72→        </dependency>\n    73→        <dependency>\n    74→            <groupId>org.reflections</groupId>\n    75→            <artifactId>reflections</artifactId>\n    76→            <version>0.10.2</version>\n    77→        </dependency>\n    78→        <dependency>\n    79→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    80→            <artifactId>quarkus-smallrye-jwt</artifactId>\n    81→        </dependency>\n    82→        <dependency>\n    83→            <groupId>org.projectlombok</groupId>\n    84→            <artifactId>lombok</artifactId>\n    85→            <version>1.18.38</version>\n    86→            <scope>provided</scope>\n    87→        </dependency>\n    88→        <dependency>\n    89→            <groupId>com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype</groupId>\n    90→            <artifactId>jackson-datatype-jsr310</artifactId>\n    91→        </dependency>\n    92→        <dependency>\n    93→            <groupId>com.github.slugify</groupId>\n    94→            <artifactId>slugify</artifactId>\n    95→            <version>3.0.7</version>\n    96→        </dependency>\n    97→        <dependency>\n    98→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    99→            <artifactId>quarkus-hibernate-orm-panache</artifactId>\n   100→        </dependency>\n   101→        <dependency>\n   102→            <groupId>org.apache.commons</groupId>\n   103→            <artifactId>commons-lang3</artifactId>\n   104→        </dependency>\n   105→    </dependencies>\n   106→    <build>\n   107→        <plugins>\n   108→            <plugin>\n   109→                <groupId>com.diffplug.spotless</groupId>\n   110→                <artifactId>spotless-maven-plugin</artifactId>\n   111→                <version>${spotless.version}</version>\n   112→                <executions>\n   113→                    <execution>\n   114→                        <goals>\n   115→                            <goal>apply</goal>\n   116→                        </goals>\n   117→                        <phase>validate</phase>\n   118→                    </execution>\n   119→                </executions>\n   120→                <configuration>\n   121→                    <java>\n   122→                        <googleJavaFormat/>\n   123→                        <removeUnusedImports/>\n   124→                    </java>\n   125→                </configuration>\n   126→            </plugin>\n   127→            <plugin>\n   128→                <groupId>${quarkus.platform.group-id}</groupId>\n   129→                <artifactId>quarkus-maven-plugin</artifactId>\n   130→                <version>${quarkus.platform.version}</version>\n   131→                <extensions>true</extensions>\n   132→                <executions>\n   133→                    <execution>\n   134→                        <goals>\n   135→                            <goal>build</goal>\n   136→                            <goal>generate-code</goal>\n   137→                            <goal>generate-code-tests</goal>\n   138→                        </goals>\n   139→                    </execution>\n   140→                </executions>\n   141→            </plugin>\n   142→            <plugin>\n   143→                <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>\n   144→                <version>${compiler-plugin.version}</version>\n   145→                <configuration>\n   146→                    <compilerArgs>\n   147→                        <arg>-parameters</arg>\n   148→                    </compilerArgs>\n   149→                </configuration>\n   150→            </plugin>\n   151→            <plugin>\n   152→                <artifactId>maven-surefire-plugin</artifactId>\n   153→                <version>${surefire-plugin.version}</version>\n   154→                <configuration>\n   155→                    <argLine>-Duser.language=en</argLine>\n   156→                    <systemPropertyVariables>\n   157→                        <java.util.logging.manager>org.jboss.logmanager.LogManager</java.util.logging.manager>\n   158→                        <maven.home>${maven.home}</maven.home>\n   159→                    </systemPropertyVariables>\n   160→                </configuration>\n   161→            </plugin>\n   162→        </plugins>\n   163→    </build>\n   164→    <profiles>\n   165→        <profile>\n   166→            <id>native</id>\n   167→            <activation>\n   168→                <property>\n   169→                    <name>native</name>\n   170→                </property>\n   171→            </activation>\n   172→            <build>\n   173→                <plugins>\n   174→                    <plugin>\n   175→                        <artifactId>maven-failsafe-plugin</artifactId>\n   176→                        <version>${surefire-plugin.version}</version>\n   177→                        <executions>\n   178→                            <execution>\n   179→                                <goals>\n   180→                                    <goal>integration-test</goal>\n   181→                                    <goal>verify</goal>\n   182→                                </goals>\n   183→                                <configuration>\n   184→                                    <systemPropertyVariables>\n   185→                                        <native.image.path>\n   186→                                            ${project.build.directory}/${project.build.finalName}-runner\n   187→                                        </native.image.path>\n   188→                                        <java.util.logging.manager>org.jboss.logmanager.LogManager\n   189→                                        </java.util.logging.manager>\n   190→                                        <maven.home>${maven.home}</maven.home>\n   191→                                    </systemPropertyVariables>\n   192→                                </configuration>\n   193→                            </execution>\n   194→                        </executions>\n   195→                    </plugin>\n   196→                </plugins>\n   197→            </build>\n   198→            <properties>\n   199→                <quarkus.package.type>native</quarkus.package.type>\n   200→            </properties>\n   201→        </profile>\n   202→    </profiles>\n   203→</project>\n   204→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"8be951f5-3f85-4127-abfe-e3ce5de1160c"}
