{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TuvDzwqgZfumQz1X8Z3Gig","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/utils/ResourceUtils.java has been updated. Here's the result of running `cat -n` on a snippet of the edited file:\n     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.utils;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\n     6→import java.security.Principal;\n     7→import java.util.List;\n     8→import java.util.UUID;\n     9→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.*;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.*;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.PageResult;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n    15→\n    16→@ApplicationScoped\n    17→public class ResourceUtils {\n    18→\n    19→  private static final int DEFAULT_LIMIT = 20;\n    20→  @Inject private FindUserByUsername findUserByUsername;\n    21→  @Inject private IsFollowingUser isFollowingUser;\n    22→  @Inject private FindArticleTags findArticleTags;\n    23→  @Inject private IsArticleFavorited isArticleFavorited;\n    24→  @Inject private ArticleFavoritesCount articleFavoritesCount;\n    25→\n    26→  public ProfileResponse profileResponse(String username, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    27→    final var user = findUserByUsername.handle(username);\n    28→    final var profileResponse = new ProfileResponse(user);\n    29→    if (loggedUserId != null) {\n    30→      profileResponse.setFollowing(isFollowingUser.handle(loggedUserId, user.getId()));\n    31→    }\n    32→    return profileResponse;\n    33→  }\n    34→\n    35→  public ArticleResponse articleResponse(Article article, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    36→    final var author = article.getAuthor();\n    37→    final var profileResponse = profileResponse(author.getUsername(), author.getId());\n    38→    final var tags = findArticleTags.handle(article);\n    39→    final var favoritesCount = articleFavoritesCount.handle(article.getId());\n    40→    final var articleResponse = new ArticleResponse(article, profileResponse, favoritesCount, tags);\n    41→    if (loggedUserId != null) {\n    42→      articleResponse.setFavorited(isArticleFavorited.handle(article, loggedUserId));\n    43→    }\n    44→    return articleResponse;\n    45→  }\n    46→\n    47→  public ArticlesResponse articlesResponse(PageResult<Article> pageResult, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    48→    final var resultResponse =\n    49→        pageResult.getResult().stream()\n    50→            .map(article -> articleResponse(article, loggedUserId))\n    51→            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    52→    return new ArticlesResponse(resultResponse, pageResult.getTotal());\n    53→  }\n    54→\n    55→  public CommentResponse commentResponse(Comment comment, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    56→    final var commentAuthor = comment.getAuthor();\n    57→    final var authorResponse = profileResponse(commentAuthor.getUsername(), loggedUserId);\n    58→    return new CommentResponse(comment, authorResponse);\n    59→  }\n    60→\n    61→  public UUID getLoggedUserId(SecurityContext securityContext) {\n    62→    Principal principal = securityContext.getUserPrincipal();\n    63→    return principal != null ? UUID.fromString(principal.getName()) : null;\n    64→  }\n    65→\n    66→  public CommentsResponse commentsResponse(List<Comment> comments, UUID loggedUserId) {\n    67→    final var resultResponse =\n    68→        comments.stream()\n    69→            .map(comment -> commentResponse(comment, loggedUserId))\n    70→            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    71→    return new CommentsResponse(resultResponse);\n    72→  }\n    73→\n    74→  public int getLimit(int limit) {\n    75→    return limit > 0 ? limit : DEFAULT_LIMIT;\n    76→  }\n    77→}\n    78→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XkTiu9aVstQ59zWiy6Ux2C","session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"584c71a5-e1e4-4db3-8366-6b586277d70b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XkTiu9aVstQ59zWiy6Ux2C","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have successfully read and rewritten all 9 files as requested. Here's a summary of the changes made:\n\n## Summary of File Updates\n\nAll files have been successfully updated with the following changes:\n\n### 1. **BCryptHashProvider.java**\n- Replaced `io.quarkus.elytron.security.common.BcryptUtil` with `org.mindrot.jbcrypt.BCrypt`\n- Updated method implementations to use `BCrypt.hashpw()` and `BCrypt.checkpw()`\n\n### 2. **JwtTokenProvider.java**\n- Replaced SmallRye JWT with Nimbus JOSE JWT library\n- Added RSA private key loading from `privateKey.pem`\n- Implemented manual JWT token creation with RS256 signing algorithm\n- Added proper exception handling and token expiration (1 hour)\n\n### 3. **ExceptionMappers.java**\n- Replaced entire content with a comment indicating the class is no longer used\n- Removed all Quarkus-specific `@ServerExceptionMapper` annotations\n- Exception mapping now handled by BusinessExceptionMapper and GenericExceptionMapper\n\n### 4. **UsersResource.java**\n- Removed `@AllArgsConstructor` annotation\n- Replaced Lombok constructor injection with standard `@Inject` field injection\n- Changed `io.quarkus.security.UnauthorizedException` to `jakarta.ws.rs.NotAuthorizedException`\n- Updated login exception handling to throw `NotAuthorizedException` with \"Bearer\" scheme\n\n### 5. **UserResource.java**\n- Removed `@AllArgsConstructor` annotation\n- Replaced Lombok constructor injection with standard `@Inject` field injection\n\n### 6. **ArticlesResource.java**\n- Removed `@AllArgsConstructor` annotation\n- Replaced Lombok constructor injection with standard `@Inject` field injection\n- Added `@Inject` annotation to all field declarations\n\n### 7. **ProfilesResource.java**\n- Removed `@AllArgsConstructor` annotation\n- Replaced Lombok constructor injection with standard `@Inject` field injection\n\n### 8. **TagsResource.java**\n- Removed `@AllArgsConstructor` annotation\n- Replaced Lombok constructor injection with standard `@Inject` field injection\n\n### 9. **ResourceUtils.java**\n- Removed `@AllArgsConstructor` annotation\n- Replaced Lombok constructor injection with standard `@Inject` field injection\n\nAll files have been successfully migrated away from Quarkus-specific dependencies to standard Jakarta EE specifications, making the application more portable across different Jakarta EE compatible servers."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"aa34083a-3702-4ba7-9821-19daf08479b4"}
