{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JGkSwKmHX6TF7jaZ374bcV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→quarkus.rest.path=/api\n     2→\n     3→# Database configuration — PostgreSQL for all profiles.\n     4→quarkus.datasource.db-kind=postgresql\n     5→quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/realworld\n     6→quarkus.datasource.username=realworld\n     7→quarkus.datasource.password=realworld\n     8→quarkus.hibernate-orm.database.generation=drop-and-create\n     9→\n    10→# JWT settings\n    11→smallrye.jwt.sign.key.location=classpath:privateKey.pem\n    12→mp.jwt.verify.publickey.location=classpath:publicKey.pem\n    13→mp.jwt.verify.issuer=users-service\n    14→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"8f1373fb-835c-4eca-a163-c9b98575920a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KondxJ2sPvcvMRkCFb2jD4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→#!/bin/bash\n     2→set -e\n     3→\n     4→# Start PostgreSQL\n     5→pg_ctlcluster $(pg_lsclusters -h | head -1 | awk '{print $1, $2}') start\n     6→\n     7→# Create database and user\n     8→su - postgres -c \"psql -c \\\"CREATE USER realworld WITH PASSWORD 'realworld';\\\"\" 2>/dev/null || true\n     9→su - postgres -c \"psql -c \\\"CREATE DATABASE realworld OWNER realworld;\\\"\" 2>/dev/null || true\n    10→su - postgres -c \"psql -c \\\"GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE realworld TO realworld;\\\"\" 2>/dev/null || true\n    11→\n    12→exec java -jar target/quarkus-app/quarkus-run.jar\n    13→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"5ac09222-9434-4687-a8d0-882006e4ab2a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01M7uNsHqjLJJjC4pxTwgt1e","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n     2→\n     3→USER root\n     4→# install uv and PostgreSQL\n     5→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl lsof python3-venv python3-full postgresql postgresql-client \\\n     6→    && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n     7→\n     8→ENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n     9→\n    10→# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\n    11→ENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\n    12→RUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n    13→\n    14→# create venv and install\n    15→RUN uv venv /opt/venv     && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n    16→\n    17→ENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n    18→RUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n    19→\n    20→# Set working directory\n    21→WORKDIR /app\n    22→\n    23→# Copy all the assets\n    24→COPY . .\n    25→\n    26→RUN if [ -f mvnw ]; then chmod +x mvnw; fi && if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n    27→RUN chmod +x start.sh\n    28→\n    29→# Build the application at image build time\n    30→RUN mvn clean install -DskipTests\n    31→\n    32→CMD [\"/app/start.sh\"]\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"8e556118-6567-43f1-a016-c89eac34ac68"}
