{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Jhcy9wTi76oTYZ2zBmuG1e","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n     5→import java.util.HashSet;\n     6→import java.util.Set;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.*;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper.BeanValidationExceptionMapper;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper.BusinessExceptionMapper;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper.GenericExceptionMapper;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.JacksonConfigProvider;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.JwtSecurityFilter;\n    13→\n    14→@ApplicationPath(\"/api\")\n    15→public class RestApplication extends Application {\n    16→\n    17→  @Override\n    18→  public Set<Class<?>> getClasses() {\n    19→    Set<Class<?>> classes = new HashSet<>();\n    20→    // Resources\n    21→    classes.add(UsersResource.class);\n    22→    classes.add(UserResource.class);\n    23→    classes.add(ArticlesResource.class);\n    24→    classes.add(ProfilesResource.class);\n    25→    classes.add(TagsResource.class);\n    26→    classes.add(HealthResource.class);\n    27→    // Exception mappers\n    28→    classes.add(BeanValidationExceptionMapper.class);\n    29→    classes.add(BusinessExceptionMapper.class);\n    30→    classes.add(GenericExceptionMapper.class);\n    31→    // Providers\n    32→    classes.add(JacksonConfigProvider.class);\n    33→    // Security\n    34→    classes.add(JwtSecurityFilter.class);\n    35→    return classes;\n    36→  }\n    37→}\n    38→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"e0d2cdb7-522a-40b6-b876-60aa86a5615f"}
