{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RBhYBRd9AZuFdtXZBiMXyW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n     2→<project xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 https://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\"\n     3→         xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\"\n     4→         xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\">\n     5→    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n     6→    <groupId>org.example</groupId>\n     7→    <artifactId>realworldapiservice</artifactId>\n     8→    <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>\n     9→    <packaging>jar</packaging>\n    10→\n    11→    <properties>\n    12→        <compiler-plugin.version>3.14.0</compiler-plugin.version>\n    13→        <maven.compiler.release>21</maven.compiler.release>\n    14→        <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n    15→        <project.reporting.outputEncoding>UTF-8</project.reporting.outputEncoding>\n    16→        <surefire-plugin.version>3.5.3</surefire-plugin.version>\n    17→        <spotless.version>2.46.1</spotless.version>\n    18→        <!-- Jakarta EE / Runtime versions -->\n    19→        <resteasy.version>6.2.12.Final</resteasy.version>\n    20→        <weld.version>5.1.3.Final</weld.version>\n    21→        <hibernate.version>6.6.4.Final</hibernate.version>\n    22→        <hibernate-validator.version>8.0.2.Final</hibernate-validator.version>\n    23→        <undertow.version>2.3.18.Final</undertow.version>\n    24→        <jackson.version>2.18.2</jackson.version>\n    25→        <jboss-logging.version>3.6.1.Final</jboss-logging.version>\n    26→    </properties>\n    27→\n    28→    <dependencies>\n    29→        <!-- Jakarta EE APIs -->\n    30→        <dependency>\n    31→            <groupId>jakarta.platform</groupId>\n    32→            <artifactId>jakarta.jakartaee-api</artifactId>\n    33→            <version>10.0.0</version>\n    34→            <scope>provided</scope>\n    35→        </dependency>\n    36→\n    37→        <!-- Undertow embedded server -->\n    38→        <dependency>\n    39→            <groupId>io.undertow</groupId>\n    40→            <artifactId>undertow-core</artifactId>\n    41→            <version>${undertow.version}</version>\n    42→        </dependency>\n    43→        <dependency>\n    44→            <groupId>io.undertow</groupId>\n    45→            <artifactId>undertow-servlet</artifactId>\n    46→            <version>${undertow.version}</version>\n    47→        </dependency>\n    48→\n    49→        <!-- RESTEasy (JAX-RS) -->\n    50→        <dependency>\n    51→            <groupId>org.jboss.resteasy</groupId>\n    52→            <artifactId>resteasy-undertow</artifactId>\n    53→            <version>${resteasy.version}</version>\n    54→        </dependency>\n    55→        <dependency>\n    56→            <groupId>org.jboss.resteasy</groupId>\n    57→            <artifactId>resteasy-jackson2-provider</artifactId>\n    58→            <version>${resteasy.version}</version>\n    59→        </dependency>\n    60→        <dependency>\n    61→            <groupId>org.jboss.resteasy</groupId>\n    62→            <artifactId>resteasy-cdi</artifactId>\n    63→            <version>${resteasy.version}</version>\n    64→        </dependency>\n    65→        <dependency>\n    66→            <groupId>org.jboss.resteasy</groupId>\n    67→            <artifactId>resteasy-validator-provider</artifactId>\n    68→            <version>${resteasy.version}</version>\n    69→        </dependency>\n    70→\n    71→        <!-- Weld (CDI) -->\n    72→        <dependency>\n    73→            <groupId>org.jboss.weld.se</groupId>\n    74→            <artifactId>weld-se-core</artifactId>\n    75→            <version>${weld.version}</version>\n    76→        </dependency>\n    77→        <dependency>\n    78→            <groupId>org.jboss.weld.servlet</groupId>\n    79→            <artifactId>weld-servlet-core</artifactId>\n    80→            <version>${weld.version}</version>\n    81→        </dependency>\n    82→\n    83→        <!-- Hibernate ORM -->\n    84→        <dependency>\n    85→            <groupId>org.hibernate.orm</groupId>\n    86→            <artifactId>hibernate-core</artifactId>\n    87→            <version>${hibernate.version}</version>\n    88→        </dependency>\n    89→\n    90→        <!-- Hibernate Validator -->\n    91→        <dependency>\n    92→            <groupId>org.hibernate.validator</groupId>\n    93→            <artifactId>hibernate-validator</artifactId>\n    94→            <version>${hibernate-validator.version}</version>\n    95→        </dependency>\n    96→        <dependency>\n    97→            <groupId>org.glassfish.expressly</groupId>\n    98→            <artifactId>expressly</artifactId>\n    99→            <version>5.0.0</version>\n   100→        </dependency>\n   101→\n   102→        <!-- PostgreSQL JDBC -->\n   103→        <dependency>\n   104→            <groupId>org.postgresql</groupId>\n   105→            <artifactId>postgresql</artifactId>\n   106→            <version>42.7.4</version>\n   107→        </dependency>\n   108→\n   109→        <!-- Jackson -->\n   110→        <dependency>\n   111→            <groupId>com.fasterxml.jackson.core</groupId>\n   112→            <artifactId>jackson-databind</artifactId>\n   113→            <version>${jackson.version}</version>\n   114→        </dependency>\n   115→        <dependency>\n   116→            <groupId>com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype</groupId>\n   117→            <artifactId>jackson-datatype-jsr310</artifactId>\n   118→            <version>${jackson.version}</version>\n   119→        </dependency>\n   120→        <dependency>\n   121→            <groupId>com.fasterxml.jackson.core</groupId>\n   122→            <artifactId>jackson-annotations</artifactId>\n   123→            <version>${jackson.version}</version>\n   124→        </dependency>\n   125→\n   126→        <!-- JWT - Nimbus JOSE -->\n   127→        <dependency>\n   128→            <groupId>com.nimbusds</groupId>\n   129→            <artifactId>nimbus-jose-jwt</artifactId>\n   130→            <version>9.47</version>\n   131→        </dependency>\n   132→\n   133→        <!-- BCrypt -->\n   134→        <dependency>\n   135→            <groupId>org.mindrot</groupId>\n   136→            <artifactId>jbcrypt</artifactId>\n   137→            <version>0.4</version>\n   138→        </dependency>\n   139→\n   140→        <!-- Slugify -->\n   141→        <dependency>\n   142→            <groupId>com.github.slugify</groupId>\n   143→            <artifactId>slugify</artifactId>\n   144→            <version>3.0.7</version>\n   145→        </dependency>\n   146→\n   147→        <!-- Lombok -->\n   148→        <dependency>\n   149→            <groupId>org.projectlombok</groupId>\n   150→            <artifactId>lombok</artifactId>\n   151→            <version>1.18.38</version>\n   152→            <scope>provided</scope>\n   153→        </dependency>\n   154→\n   155→        <!-- Commons Lang -->\n   156→        <dependency>\n   157→            <groupId>org.apache.commons</groupId>\n   158→            <artifactId>commons-lang3</artifactId>\n   159→            <version>3.17.0</version>\n   160→        </dependency>\n   161→\n   162→        <!-- Reflections -->\n   163→        <dependency>\n   164→            <groupId>org.reflections</groupId>\n   165→            <artifactId>reflections</artifactId>\n   166→            <version>0.10.2</version>\n   167→        </dependency>\n   168→\n   169→        <!-- JBoss Transaction SPI for Weld/JTA integration -->\n   170→        <dependency>\n   171→            <groupId>org.jboss</groupId>\n   172→            <artifactId>jboss-transaction-spi</artifactId>\n   173→            <version>8.0.0.Final</version>\n   174→        </dependency>\n   175→        <dependency>\n   176→            <groupId>jakarta.transaction</groupId>\n   177→            <artifactId>jakarta.transaction-api</artifactId>\n   178→            <version>2.0.1</version>\n   179→        </dependency>\n   180→\n   181→        <!-- Logging -->\n   182→        <dependency>\n   183→            <groupId>org.jboss.logging</groupId>\n   184→            <artifactId>jboss-logging</artifactId>\n   185→            <version>${jboss-logging.version}</version>\n   186→        </dependency>\n   187→        <dependency>\n   188→            <groupId>org.slf4j</groupId>\n   189→            <artifactId>slf4j-api</artifactId>\n   190→            <version>2.0.16</version>\n   191→        </dependency>\n   192→        <dependency>\n   193→            <groupId>org.slf4j</groupId>\n   194→            <artifactId>slf4j-simple</artifactId>\n   195→            <version>2.0.16</version>\n   196→        </dependency>\n   197→\n   198→        <!-- Test dependencies -->\n   199→        <dependency>\n   200→            <groupId>org.junit.jupiter</groupId>\n   201→            <artifactId>junit-jupiter</artifactId>\n   202→            <version>5.11.4</version>\n   203→            <scope>test</scope>\n   204→        </dependency>\n   205→        <dependency>\n   206→            <groupId>io.rest-assured</groupId>\n   207→            <artifactId>rest-assured</artifactId>\n   208→            <version>5.5.0</version>\n   209→            <scope>test</scope>\n   210→        </dependency>\n   211→    </dependencies>\n   212→\n   213→    <build>\n   214→        <plugins>\n   215→            <plugin>\n   216→                <groupId>com.diffplug.spotless</groupId>\n   217→                <artifactId>spotless-maven-plugin</artifactId>\n   218→                <version>${spotless.version}</version>\n   219→                <executions>\n   220→                    <execution>\n   221→                        <goals>\n   222→                            <goal>apply</goal>\n   223→                        </goals>\n   224→                        <phase>validate</phase>\n   225→                    </execution>\n   226→                </executions>\n   227→                <configuration>\n   228→                    <java>\n   229→                        <googleJavaFormat/>\n   230→                        <removeUnusedImports/>\n   231→                    </java>\n   232→                </configuration>\n   233→            </plugin>\n   234→            <plugin>\n   235→                <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>\n   236→                <version>${compiler-plugin.version}</version>\n   237→                <configuration>\n   238→                    <compilerArgs>\n   239→                        <arg>-parameters</arg>\n   240→                    </compilerArgs>\n   241→                    <annotationProcessorPaths>\n   242→                        <path>\n   243→                            <groupId>org.projectlombok</groupId>\n   244→                            <artifactId>lombok</artifactId>\n   245→                            <version>1.18.38</version>\n   246→                        </path>\n   247→                    </annotationProcessorPaths>\n   248→                </configuration>\n   249→            </plugin>\n   250→            <plugin>\n   251→                <artifactId>maven-surefire-plugin</artifactId>\n   252→                <version>${surefire-plugin.version}</version>\n   253→                <configuration>\n   254→                    <argLine>-Duser.language=en</argLine>\n   255→                </configuration>\n   256→            </plugin>\n   257→            <!-- Create fat JAR -->\n   258→            <plugin>\n   259→                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>\n   260→                <artifactId>maven-shade-plugin</artifactId>\n   261→                <version>3.6.0</version>\n   262→                <executions>\n   263→                    <execution>\n   264→                        <phase>package</phase>\n   265→                        <goals>\n   266→                            <goal>shade</goal>\n   267→                        </goals>\n   268→                        <configuration>\n   269→                            <createDependencyReducedPom>false</createDependencyReducedPom>\n   270→                            <transformers>\n   271→                                <transformer implementation=\"org.apache.maven.plugins.shade.resource.ManifestResourceTransformer\">\n   272→                                    <mainClass>org.example.realworldapi.Main</mainClass>\n   273→                                </transformer>\n   274→                                <transformer implementation=\"org.apache.maven.plugins.shade.resource.ServicesResourceTransformer\"/>\n   275→                                <transformer implementation=\"org.apache.maven.plugins.shade.resource.AppendingTransformer\">\n   276→                                    <resource>META-INF/beans.xml</resource>\n   277→                                </transformer>\n   278→                            </transformers>\n   279→                            <filters>\n   280→                                <filter>\n   281→                                    <artifact>*:*</artifact>\n   282→                                    <excludes>\n   283→                                        <exclude>META-INF/*.SF</exclude>\n   284→                                        <exclude>META-INF/*.DSA</exclude>\n   285→                                        <exclude>META-INF/*.RSA</exclude>\n   286→                                        <exclude>module-info.class</exclude>\n   287→                                    </excludes>\n   288→                                </filter>\n   289→                            </filters>\n   290→                        </configuration>\n   291→                    </execution>\n   292→                </executions>\n   293→            </plugin>\n   294→        </plugins>\n   295→    </build>\n   296→</project>\n   297→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"3cee0ee1-94ea-4ff2-9782-5c0d47a03fcc"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UC8rKAfzHRisLeUG3EKK4E","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security;\n     2→\n     3→import com.nimbusds.jose.JWSVerifier;\n     4→import com.nimbusds.jose.crypto.RSASSAVerifier;\n     5→import com.nimbusds.jwt.SignedJWT;\n     6→import jakarta.annotation.Priority;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.Priorities;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ContainerRequestContext;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ContainerRequestFilter;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.Provider;\n    11→import java.io.InputStream;\n    12→import java.security.KeyFactory;\n    13→import java.security.interfaces.RSAPublicKey;\n    14→import java.security.spec.X509EncodedKeySpec;\n    15→import java.util.*;\n    16→\n    17→@Provider\n    18→@Priority(Priorities.AUTHENTICATION)\n    19→public class JwtSecurityFilter implements ContainerRequestFilter {\n    20→\n    21→  private RSAPublicKey publicKey;\n    22→\n    23→  public JwtSecurityFilter() {\n    24→    try {\n    25→      this.publicKey = loadPublicKey();\n    26→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    27→      System.err.println(\"Warning: Could not load JWT public key: \" + e.getMessage());\n    28→    }\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  @Override\n    32→  public void filter(ContainerRequestContext requestContext) {\n    33→    String authHeader = requestContext.getHeaderString(\"Authorization\");\n    34→    if (authHeader != null && authHeader.startsWith(\"Token \")) {\n    35→      String token = authHeader.substring(6).trim();\n    36→      try {\n    37→        SignedJWT signedJWT = SignedJWT.parse(token);\n    38→        if (publicKey != null) {\n    39→          JWSVerifier verifier = new RSASSAVerifier(publicKey);\n    40→          if (signedJWT.verify(verifier)) {\n    41→            String subject = signedJWT.getJWTClaimsSet().getSubject();\n    42→            List<String> groups =\n    43→                signedJWT.getJWTClaimsSet().getStringListClaim(\"groups\");\n    44→            if (groups == null) {\n    45→              groups = List.of(\"USER\");\n    46→            }\n    47→            requestContext.setSecurityContext(\n    48→                new JwtSecurityContext(subject, groups, requestContext.getSecurityContext()));\n    49→          }\n    50→        }\n    51→      } catch (Exception e) {\n    52→        // Invalid token - continue without authentication\n    53→      }\n    54→    } else if (authHeader != null && authHeader.startsWith(\"Bearer \")) {\n    55→      String token = authHeader.substring(7).trim();\n    56→      try {\n    57→        SignedJWT signedJWT = SignedJWT.parse(token);\n    58→        if (publicKey != null) {\n    59→          JWSVerifier verifier = new RSASSAVerifier(publicKey);\n    60→          if (signedJWT.verify(verifier)) {\n    61→            String subject = signedJWT.getJWTClaimsSet().getSubject();\n    62→            List<String> groups =\n    63→                signedJWT.getJWTClaimsSet().getStringListClaim(\"groups\");\n    64→            if (groups == null) {\n    65→              groups = List.of(\"USER\");\n    66→            }\n    67→            requestContext.setSecurityContext(\n    68→                new JwtSecurityContext(subject, groups, requestContext.getSecurityContext()));\n    69→          }\n    70→        }\n    71→      } catch (Exception e) {\n    72→        // Invalid token - continue without authentication\n    73→      }\n    74→    }\n    75→  }\n    76→\n    77→  private RSAPublicKey loadPublicKey() throws Exception {\n    78→    try (InputStream is =\n    79→        Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader().getResourceAsStream(\"publicKey.pem\")) {\n    80→      if (is == null) {\n    81→        throw new RuntimeException(\"publicKey.pem not found in classpath\");\n    82→      }\n    83→      String pem = new String(is.readAllBytes());\n    84→      pem =\n    85→          pem.replace(\"-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----\", \"\")\n    86→              .replace(\"-----END PUBLIC KEY-----\", \"\")\n    87→              .replaceAll(\"\\\\s\", \"\");\n    88→      byte[] decoded = Base64.getDecoder().decode(pem);\n    89→      X509EncodedKeySpec spec = new X509EncodedKeySpec(decoded);\n    90→      KeyFactory kf = KeyFactory.getInstance(\"RSA\");\n    91→      return (RSAPublicKey) kf.generatePublic(spec);\n    92→    }\n    93→  }\n    94→}\n    95→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"aa2e878a-0cb4-4f4a-8467-a6729292a85f"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01TaaEvQbVvd7cj2ZqRWbat6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I need to fix the ambiguous `EntityManager` producer issue. The `EntityManagerFactoryProducer` produces a `@TransactionScoped EntityManager` (which is a qualifier, not a scope - so it won't match plain `@Inject EntityManager`), while `EntityManagerProducer` produces an unqualified `@RequestScoped EntityManager`. The repositories inject plain `@Inject EntityManager`, so they'll get the one from `EntityManagerProducer`. However, having the `@TransactionScoped` producer in `EntityManagerFactoryProducer` is unnecessary and confusing. Let me clean this up, and also check other important files before proceeding."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6524,"cache_read_input_tokens":34741,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6524,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":608},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"67b6cde5-6559-4f76-9756-7b597a27aaee"}
