{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0145rh4yPooRGYtAHfbPqL5s","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n     2→\n     3→import com.nimbusds.jose.JWSAlgorithm;\n     4→import com.nimbusds.jose.JWSHeader;\n     5→import com.nimbusds.jose.crypto.RSASSASigner;\n     6→import com.nimbusds.jwt.JWTClaimsSet;\n     7→import com.nimbusds.jwt.SignedJWT;\n     8→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     9→import java.io.InputStream;\n    10→import java.security.KeyFactory;\n    11→import java.security.interfaces.RSAPrivateKey;\n    12→import java.security.spec.PKCS8EncodedKeySpec;\n    13→import java.util.*;\n    14→\n    15→@ApplicationScoped\n    16→public class JwtTokenProvider {\n    17→\n    18→  private RSAPrivateKey privateKey;\n    19→\n    20→  public JwtTokenProvider() {\n    21→    try {\n    22→      this.privateKey = loadPrivateKey();\n    23→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    24→      System.err.println(\"Warning: Could not load JWT private key: \" + e.getMessage());\n    25→    }\n    26→  }\n    27→\n    28→  public String createUserToken(String subject) {\n    29→    try {\n    30→      JWTClaimsSet claimsSet =\n    31→          new JWTClaimsSet.Builder()\n    32→              .issuer(\"users-service\")\n    33→              .subject(subject)\n    34→              .claim(\"groups\", List.of(\"USER\"))\n    35→              .expirationTime(new Date(System.currentTimeMillis() + 3600 * 1000))\n    36→              .issueTime(new Date())\n    37→              .build();\n    38→\n    39→      SignedJWT signedJWT = new SignedJWT(new JWSHeader(JWSAlgorithm.RS256), claimsSet);\n    40→      signedJWT.sign(new RSASSASigner(privateKey));\n    41→      return signedJWT.serialize();\n    42→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    43→      throw new RuntimeException(\"Failed to create JWT token\", e);\n    44→    }\n    45→  }\n    46→\n    47→  private RSAPrivateKey loadPrivateKey() throws Exception {\n    48→    try (InputStream is =\n    49→        Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader().getResourceAsStream(\"privateKey.pem\")) {\n    50→      if (is == null) {\n    51→        throw new RuntimeException(\"privateKey.pem not found in classpath\");\n    52→      }\n    53→      String pem = new String(is.readAllBytes());\n    54→      pem =\n    55→          pem.replace(\"-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\", \"\")\n    56→              .replace(\"-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\", \"\")\n    57→              .replace(\"-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\", \"\")\n    58→              .replace(\"-----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\", \"\")\n    59→              .replaceAll(\"\\\\s\", \"\");\n    60→      byte[] decoded = Base64.getDecoder().decode(pem);\n    61→      PKCS8EncodedKeySpec spec = new PKCS8EncodedKeySpec(decoded);\n    62→      KeyFactory kf = KeyFactory.getInstance(\"RSA\");\n    63→      return (RSAPrivateKey) kf.generatePrivate(spec);\n    64→    }\n    65→  }\n    66→}\n    67→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ES75eXdEf6iurU4fXLQrMo","session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"587d1617-7603-4050-9c65-6ce280ae3063"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ES75eXdEf6iurU4fXLQrMo","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my analysis, here's a comprehensive report of the domain feature implementation classes:\n\n### Implementation Classes Overview\n\nAll implementation classes follow a consistent pattern:\n- Annotated with `@AllArgsConstructor` for constructor-based dependency injection\n- Most are scoped with `@ApplicationScoped`\n- Use constructor injection for dependencies\n- Implement domain feature interfaces\n\n### Key Characteristics\n1. Dependency Injection: Constructor-based using Lombok's `@AllArgsConstructor`\n2. Scope: Most are `@ApplicationScoped`\n3. Generally follow the pattern of:\n   - Retrieving required entities\n   - Performing domain logic\n   - Saving or manipulating entities through repositories\n\n### Implementation Details\n\n#### Token Provider\n- Located at: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/provider/JwtTokenProvider.java`\n- Annotations: `@ApplicationScoped`\n- Responsibilities: \n  - Create JWT tokens for users\n  - Load RSA private key from classpath\n  - Generate tokens with claims like issuer, subject, groups, expiration\n\n### Notable Implementation Classes\n\n1. CreateUserImpl\n   - Repositories: UserRepository\n   - Providers: HashProvider\n   - Checks for existing username/email\n   - Hashes password before saving\n\n2. LoginUserImpl\n   - Repositories: UserRepository\n   - Providers: HashProvider\n   - Validates user credentials\n   - Throws exceptions for invalid credentials\n\n3. CreateArticleImpl\n   - Multiple repositories: ArticleRepository, TagRelationshipRepository\n   - Creates article with associated tags\n   - Generates slug for article\n\n4. FollowUserByUsernameImpl\n   - Uses multiple feature services to resolve users\n   - Creates follow relationship\n\n### Dependency Injection Pattern\n\nConsistent use of constructor injection:\n```java\n@AllArgsConstructor\npublic class SomeImpl implements SomeFeature {\n  private final SomeRepository repository;\n  private final SomeProvider provider;\n  // ... method implementations\n}\n```\n\n### Scoping\nMost classes are `@ApplicationScoped`, indicating they are singleton-scoped beans in the Jakarta EE context.\n\n### Error Handling\n- Extensive use of custom exceptions\n- Exceptions for:\n  - Not found scenarios (UserNotFoundException, ArticleNotFoundException)\n  - Validation issues (EmailAlreadyExistsException, InvalidPasswordException)\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of these implementation classes?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"3ee7ce16-3b44-4879-baa6-f6f2722b5008"}
