{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RiNcBv2n9J3o2oggL44D6J","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.configuration;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.Produces;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.*;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl.CreateCommentImpl;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl.DeleteCommentImpl;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl.FindCommentByIdAndAuthorImpl;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl.FindCommentsByArticleSlugImpl;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentBuilder;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator.ModelValidator;\n    14→\n    15→@Dependent\n    16→public class CommentsConfiguration {\n    17→\n    18→  @Produces\n    19→  @Singleton\n    20→  public CreateComment createComment(\n    21→      CommentRepository commentRepository,\n    22→      FindUserById findUserById,\n    23→      FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug,\n    24→      CommentBuilder commentBuilder) {\n    25→    return new CreateCommentImpl(\n    26→        commentRepository, findUserById, findArticleBySlug, commentBuilder);\n    27→  }\n    28→\n    29→  @Produces\n    30→  @Singleton\n    31→  public DeleteComment deleteComment(\n    32→      FindCommentByIdAndAuthor findCommentByIdAndAuthor, CommentRepository commentRepository) {\n    33→    return new DeleteCommentImpl(findCommentByIdAndAuthor, commentRepository);\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  @Produces\n    37→  @Singleton\n    38→  public FindCommentByIdAndAuthor findCommentByIdAndAuthor(CommentRepository commentRepository) {\n    39→    return new FindCommentByIdAndAuthorImpl(commentRepository);\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  @Produces\n    43→  @Singleton\n    44→  public FindCommentsByArticleSlug findCommentsByArticleSlug(\n    45→      FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug, CommentRepository commentRepository) {\n    46→    return new FindCommentsByArticleSlugImpl(findArticleBySlug, commentRepository);\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  @Produces\n    50→  @Singleton\n    51→  public CommentBuilder commentBuilder(ModelValidator modelValidator) {\n    52→    return new CommentBuilder(modelValidator);\n    53→  }\n    54→}\n    55→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"8569dba4-7bba-4b1a-9651-90009e4a213b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Kyy5Z8C3KNa9UqJQVSQjEp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.qualifiers;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Qualifier;\n     4→import java.lang.annotation.ElementType;\n     5→import java.lang.annotation.Retention;\n     6→import java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy;\n     7→import java.lang.annotation.Target;\n     8→\n     9→@Qualifier\n    10→@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n    11→@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.FIELD, ElementType.METHOD, ElementType.PARAMETER})\n    12→public @interface NoWrapRootValueObjectMapper {}\n    13→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"843b47ae-d9dd-405f-81e7-0f7f78e27fc7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011WsRan7KJDBqvZFFV2PAj9","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.provider;\n     2→\n     3→import com.github.slugify.Slugify;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     5→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.SlugProvider;\n     7→\n     8→@ApplicationScoped\n     9→@AllArgsConstructor\n    10→public class SlugifySlugProvider implements SlugProvider {\n    11→\n    12→  private final Slugify slugify;\n    13→\n    14→  @Override\n    15→  public String slugify(String text) {\n    16→    return slugify.slugify(text);\n    17→  }\n    18→}\n    19→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"2aa8cc83-a1c7-4bca-86e3-c0af93082e7b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DsobR9FerFCttoeufnYfyK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.hibernate.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleModelBuilder;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentBuilder;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagBuilder;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.UserModelBuilder;\n    14→\n    15→@ApplicationScoped\n    16→@AllArgsConstructor\n    17→public class EntityUtils {\n    18→  private final UserModelBuilder userBuilder;\n    19→  private final TagBuilder tagBuilder;\n    20→  private final ArticleModelBuilder articleBuilder;\n    21→  private final CommentBuilder commentBuilder;\n    22→\n    23→  public User user(UserEntity userEntity) {\n    24→    final var id = userEntity.getId();\n    25→    final var username = userEntity.getUsername();\n    26→    final var bio = userEntity.getBio();\n    27→    final var image = userEntity.getImage();\n    28→    final var password = userEntity.getPassword();\n    29→    final var email = userEntity.getEmail();\n    30→    return userBuilder.build(id, username, bio, image, password, email);\n    31→  }\n    32→\n    33→  public Tag tag(TagEntity tagEntity) {\n    34→    return tagBuilder.build(tagEntity.getId(), tagEntity.getName());\n    35→  }\n    36→\n    37→  public Tag tag(TagRelationshipEntity tagRelationshipEntity) {\n    38→    return tag(tagRelationshipEntity.getPrimaryKey().getTag());\n    39→  }\n    40→\n    41→  public Article article(ArticleEntity articleEntity) {\n    42→    return articleBuilder.build(\n    43→        articleEntity.getId(),\n    44→        articleEntity.getSlug(),\n    45→        articleEntity.getTitle(),\n    46→        articleEntity.getDescription(),\n    47→        articleEntity.getBody(),\n    48→        articleEntity.getCreatedAt(),\n    49→        articleEntity.getUpdatedAt(),\n    50→        user(articleEntity.getAuthor()));\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  public Comment comment(CommentEntity commentEntity) {\n    54→    return commentBuilder.build(\n    55→        commentEntity.getId(),\n    56→        user(commentEntity.getAuthor()),\n    57→        article(commentEntity.getArticle()),\n    58→        commentEntity.getBody(),\n    59→        commentEntity.getCreatedAt(),\n    60→        commentEntity.getUpdatedAt());\n    61→  }\n    62→\n    63→  public FavoriteRelationship favoriteRelationship(\n    64→      FavoriteRelationshipEntity favoriteRelationshipEntity) {\n    65→    return new FavoriteRelationship(\n    66→        user(favoriteRelationshipEntity.getUser()),\n    67→        article(favoriteRelationshipEntity.getArticle()));\n    68→  }\n    69→}\n    70→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"09b8c0a9-6a94-47fb-9d80-47481fb75c77"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01JKkmiy3gon1UUDfNmsagYV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the codebase state. There are several issues to address:\n\n1. **`EntityUtils` and `SlugifySlugProvider`** use `@AllArgsConstructor` for CDI injection. Weld SE requires either a no-arg constructor or `@Inject` on the constructor. With `@ApplicationScoped` + `@AllArgsConstructor`, CDI needs a proxy (which requires a no-arg constructor) AND an `@Inject`-annotated constructor. I need to add `@lombok.NoArgsConstructor(force = true)` or switch to `@Inject` field injection.\n\n2. **`@Transactional` interceptor** - the `TransactionalInterceptor` uses `jakarta.transaction.Transactional`, but resources also use it. In a non-JTA environment this should work as a CDI interceptor binding.\n\n3. **`jakarta.jakartaee-api` is `provided` scope** - this means the actual API classes won't be in the fat JAR. Need to change to `compile` scope, or better yet, remove it since we have concrete implementations.\n\n4. **`beans.xml` with `bean-discovery-mode=\"annotated\"`** - the configuration classes use `@Dependent` which is a CDI annotation, so they'll be discovered. But the resources like `UsersResource` don't have explicit CDI annotations - they only have `@Path`. In Weld, `@Path` is not a CDI bean-defining annotation by default.\n\nLet me fix all these issues now. Let me update the todo list and start fixing:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3245,"cache_read_input_tokens":64408,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3245,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":892},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"255ee9fa-133c-4d0d-ba49-6c4e308e11bc"}
