{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011nath6aN1f1BiWmWt3ZcWe","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.persistence;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n     5→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.Disposes;\n     6→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.Produces;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     8→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManagerFactory;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.Persistence;\n    10→\n    11→@Dependent\n    12→public class EntityManagerFactoryProducer {\n    13→\n    14→  private static volatile EntityManagerFactory emf;\n    15→\n    16→  public static void initialize() {\n    17→    if (emf == null) {\n    18→      synchronized (EntityManagerFactoryProducer.class) {\n    19→        if (emf == null) {\n    20→          emf = Persistence.createEntityManagerFactory(\"realworld\");\n    21→        }\n    22→      }\n    23→    }\n    24→  }\n    25→\n    26→  @Produces\n    27→  @ApplicationScoped\n    28→  public EntityManagerFactory createEntityManagerFactory() {\n    29→    initialize();\n    30→    return emf;\n    31→  }\n    32→\n    33→  @Produces\n    34→  @TransactionScoped\n    35→  public EntityManager createEntityManager(EntityManagerFactory emf) {\n    36→    return emf.createEntityManager();\n    37→  }\n    38→\n    39→  public void closeEntityManager(@Disposes @TransactionScoped EntityManager em) {\n    40→    if (em.isOpen()) {\n    41→      em.close();\n    42→    }\n    43→  }\n    44→}\n    45→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_t