{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01EgfFu4KncLhQ8BdGRmd3ED","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now update the `TransactionalInterceptor` to use a custom interceptor binding instead of `jakarta.transaction.Transactional` (which won't work properly without JTA). I'll create a custom `@Transactional` alternative that works with RESOURCE_LOCAL:\n\nActually, `jakarta.transaction.Transactional` IS a valid CDI interceptor binding even without JTA - it's defined in the Jakarta Transaction API. The key issue is that Weld needs to see it as an interceptor binding. Let me reconsider - the simpler approach is to just use it as-is, since we have `jakarta.transaction-api` in our dependencies. The `TransactionalInterceptor` should work. But there could be conflicts if any framework also tries to handle `@Transactional`. Let me keep this approach but ensure the interceptor is properly enabled in `beans.xml`:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":760,"cache_read_input_tokens":76273,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":760,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":311},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"de2ea7a8-4167-43c8-912b-f5f807df15f1"}
