{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WHiTHKMRWkHw4jLnnXtJxr","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi;\n     2→\n     3→import io.undertow.Undertow;\n     4→import io.undertow.servlet.Servlets;\n     5→import io.undertow.servlet.api.DeploymentInfo;\n     6→import io.undertow.servlet.api.DeploymentManager;\n     7→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n     8→import org.jboss.resteasy.plugins.server.undertow.UndertowJaxrsServer;\n     9→import org.jboss.weld.environment.servlet.Listener;\n    10→\n    11→public class Main {\n    12→\n    13→  public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {\n    14→    // Initialize Hibernate EntityManagerFactory early\n    15→    org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.persistence.EntityManagerFactoryProducer.initialize();\n    16→\n    17→    UndertowJaxrsServer server = new UndertowJaxrsServer();\n    18→\n    19→    Undertow.Builder builder =\n    20→        Undertow.builder().addHttpListener(8080, \"0.0.0.0\").setWorkerThreads(50);\n    21→\n    22→    server.start(builder);\n    23→\n    24→    DeploymentInfo di =\n    25→        server\n    26→            .undertowDeployment(RestApplication.class)\n    27→            .setClassLoader(Main.class.getClassLoader())\n    28→            .setContextPath(\"/\")\n    29→            .setDeploymentName(\"RealWorldAPI\")\n    30→            .addListener(Servlets.listener(Listener.class));\n    31→\n    32→    DeploymentManager manager = Servlets.defaultContainer().addDeployment(di);\n    33→    manager.deploy();\n    34→\n    35→    server.addDeployment(di);\n    36→\n    37→    System.out.println(\"RealWorld API started on http://0.0.0.0:8080\");\n    38→    System.out.println(\"API base path: /api\");\n    39→  }\n    40→}\n    41→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"e4b00a6e-1a2d-4b11-a136-85f27164f0b9"}
