{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01UW5gtdTtjZ839HGKmzvA4w","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"`this.createUser` is null! The CDI injection is not working for the resource classes. This is because the resource classes are registered via `getClasses()` in the JAX-RS Application, and RESTEasy creates instances without CDI integration. The fix is to **not** register the resources in `getClasses()`, and instead let the CDI-RESTEasy integration discover them automatically, OR register them as CDI-managed singletons.\n\nThe issue is that when `getClasses()` returns classes, RESTEasy creates new instances itself (without CDI). To make CDI work with RESTEasy, I need to either:\n1. Use `getSingletons()` returning CDI-produced instances\n2. Or let RESTEasy-CDI auto-discover by returning empty sets\n3. Or use `@RequestScoped` on resources and don't override `getClasses()`\n\nThe simplest fix: Return an empty set from `getClasses()` and let RESTEasy-CDI scan for JAX-RS resources. But we still need to register providers/filters explicitly. Let me fix the `RestApplication`:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":475,"cache_read_input_tokens":148256,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":475,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":375},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"9af24107-110e-4a5c-b2f1-7e169a5b1836"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01UW5gtdTtjZ839HGKmzvA4w","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bb6xfp824Y1Ns41A4jvFbD","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/RestApplication.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":475,"cache_read_input_tokens":148256,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":475,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":375},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"289bd951-0f03-4ba0-99c8-033165117c70"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Bb6xfp824Y1Ns41A4jvFbD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n     5→import java.util.HashSet;\n     6→import java.util.Set;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.resource.*;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper.BeanValidationExceptionMapper;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper.BusinessExceptionMapper;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper.GenericExceptionMapper;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.JacksonConfigProvider;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.JwtSecurityFilter;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.RolesAllowedFilter;\n    14→\n    15→@ApplicationPath(\"/api\")\n    16→public class RestApplication extends Application {\n    17→\n    18→  @Override\n    19→  public Set<Class<?>> getClasses() {\n    20→    Set<Class<?>> classes = new HashSet<>();\n    21→    // Resources\n    22→    classes.add(UsersResource.class);\n    23→    classes.add(UserResource.class);\n    24→    classes.add(ArticlesResource.class);\n    25→    classes.add(ProfilesResource.class);\n    26→    classes.add(TagsResource.class);\n    27→    classes.add(HealthResource.class);\n    28→    // Exception mappers\n    29→    classes.add(BeanValidationExceptionMapper.class);\n    30→    classes.add(BusinessExceptionMapper.class);\n    31→    classes.add(GenericExceptionMapper.class);\n    32→    // Providers\n    33→    classes.add(JacksonConfigProvider.class);\n    34→    // Security\n    35→    classes.add(JwtSecurityFilter.class);\n    36→    classes.add(RolesAllowedFilter.class);\n    37→    return classes;\n    38→  }\n    39→}\n    40→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"753976e1-a258-4ec4-bbb0-7f664629d2fa"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Y4GdF4eyMh5hXdfjetSdaZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem is clear. When `getClasses()` is non-empty, RESTEasy creates its own instances, bypassing CDI. I need to NOT return resource classes in `getClasses()` so RESTEasy-CDI can manage them. I should either:\n- Override `getClasses()` to return only providers/filters (not resources), OR\n- Don't override `getClasses()` at all and add `@Provider` annotations + classpath scanning\n\nThe cleanest approach: only register providers/mappers/filters in `getClasses()`, and let RESTEasy-CDI auto-discover the `@Path` annotated resources. But RESTEasy needs to know about the resources somehow. With `resteasy-cdi`, if we don't override `getClasses()`, RESTEasy will scan the classpath.\n\nActually, the issue is more nuanced: when `getClasses()` returns a non-empty set, RESTEasy uses ONLY those classes and doesn't scan further. So if I return only providers, it won't find resources either.\n\nThe best approach: Don't override `getClasses()` at all, which triggers classpath scanning. RESTEasy-CDI will then discover all `@Path` and `@Provider` annotated classes automatically:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1380,"cache_read_input_tokens":148731,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1380,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":499},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"b76306ad-ef2c-4d68-be38-766260a524d4"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Y4GdF4eyMh5hXdfjetSdaZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01JNch7Mi9n5QjTN1HrWMhGB","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/RestApplication.java","content":"package org.example.realworldapi;\n\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n\n@ApplicationPath(\"/api\")\npublic class RestApplication extends Application {\n  // Let RESTEasy-CDI auto-discover @Path and @Provider annotated classes\n}\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1380,"cache_read_input_tokens":148731,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1380,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":499},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"e089e50a-5784-4050-ba66-b98c8a03d4da"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JNch7Mi9n5QjTN1HrWMhGB","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/RestApplication.java has been updated. Here's the result of running `cat -n` on a snippet of the edited file:\n     1→package org.example.realworldapi;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n     5→\n     6→@ApplicationPath(\"/api\")\n     7→public class RestApplication extends Application {\n     8→  // Let RESTEasy-CDI auto-discover @Path and @Provider annotated classes\n     9→}\n    10→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"acbf729d-b6b8-47ca-a210-5d84b5abcf98"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01LsUDrbJ9BtEQSv1MVF65NF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I also need to make sure the resource classes and providers have proper CDI annotations. The resources don't have `@RequestScoped` or any CDI scope, but with `bean-discovery-mode=\"all\"` they should be discovered as `@Dependent` beans (the default). RESTEasy-CDI typically needs `@RequestScoped` on resource classes. Let me add `@RequestScoped` to all resource classes:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":708,"cache_read_input_tokens":150111,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":708,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":549},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"e77939ea-a0c0-41fe-8b47-5c0323cc04b6"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01LsUDrbJ9BtEQSv1MVF65NF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01UDP6sEFKrQpVrYVbyMk7yQ","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Add @RequestScoped to resources","subagent_type":"general-purpose","prompt":"I need to add `@jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped` annotation to the following Java resource files. For each file:\n1. Read the file\n2. Add `import jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;` to the imports (if not already present)\n3. Add `@RequestScoped` annotation right before the class declaration line (before `public class`)\n4. Write the file back\n\nFiles to modify (all under /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/):\n1. UsersResource.java\n2. UserResource.java\n3. ArticlesResource.java\n4. ProfilesResource.java\n5. TagsResource.java\n6. HealthResource.java\n\nMake sure to preserve all existing annotations on the class (like @Path). The @RequestScoped should come before @Path.\n\nAlso add @RequestScoped to:\n7. /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/application/web/resource/utils/ResourceUtils.java - but this one already has @ApplicationScoped, so leave it unchanged.\n\nOnly modify the 6 resource files. Report back what you changed."}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":708,"cache_read_input_tokens":150111,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":708,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":549},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"83402c4a-205c-4db0-9bba-b302001d5a90"}
