{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MHFM96tXtTQbpYvzQJbPDD","type":"tool_result","content":"java.nio.file.NoSuchFileException: target/realworldapiservice-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar\n\tat java.base/sun.nio.fs.UnixException.translateToIOException(UnixException.java:92)\n\tat java.base/sun.nio.fs.UnixException.rethrowAsIOException(UnixException.java:106)\n\tat java.base/sun.nio.fs.UnixException.rethrowAsIOException(UnixException.java:111)\n\tat java.base/sun.nio.fs.UnixFileAttributeViews$Basic.readAttributes(UnixFileAttributeViews.java:55)\n\tat java.base/sun.nio.fs.UnixFileSystemProvider.readAttributes(UnixFileSystemProvider.java:171)\n\tat java.base/sun.nio.fs.LinuxFileSystemProvider.readAttributes(LinuxFileSystemProvider.java:99)\n\tat java.base/java.nio.file.Files.readAttributes(Files.java:1854)\n\tat java.base/java.util.zip.ZipFile$Source.get(ZipFile.java:1445)\n\tat java.base/java.util.zip.ZipFile$CleanableResource.<init>(ZipFile.java:724)\n\tat java.base/java.util.zip.ZipFile.<init>(ZipFile.java:251)\n\tat java.base/java.util.zip.ZipFile.<init>(ZipFile.java:180)\n\tat java.base/java.util.zip.ZipFile.<init>(ZipFile.java:151)\n\tat jdk.jartool/sun.tools.jar.Main.list(Main.java:1524)\n\tat jdk.jartool/sun.tools.jar.Main.run(Main.java:370)\n\tat jdk.jartool/sun.tools.jar.Main.main(Main.java:1702)","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"69247375-9e91-44b8-8c90-65ef9133406e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_019V6Xg6K6jbJVgjiSh19oqS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The JAR is built inside Docker. The problem is clear from the stack trace: `org/jboss/jandex/Indexer.indexWithSummary` - the class that's loaded is from `org.jboss.jandex` package (old), not `io.smallrye.jandex` (new). The issue is that Hibernate calls the old package name `org.jboss.jandex.Indexer` but the new SmallRye Jandex uses a different package. \n\nWait - actually SmallRye Jandex 3.x relocated the classes but kept the `org.jboss.jandex` package for compatibility. Let me look at the error more carefully. The error says `NoSuchMethodError: org/jboss/jandex/Indexer.indexWithSummary` - this method exists in SmallRye Jandex 3.x but NOT in the old `org.jboss:jandex:2.x`. So the old classes are winning in the shade JAR.\n\nThe issue is in how Maven Shade merges duplicate classes. Both jandex JARs have classes in the `org/jboss/jandex/` package, and the old one's classes may be overwriting the new one's. I need to check that there's not a stale `PersistenceConfiguration.java` that produces the EMF via CDI in addition to the static `EntityManagerFactoryProducer.initialize()` call in `Main.java`. But the real issue is Jandex. Let me look at what's actually happening - maybe there's a second producer for EntityManagerFactory:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1001,"cache_read_input_tokens":42330,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1001,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":603},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"37c9c01c-3988-4982-91fd-c90161405b81"}
