{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ST77a9ebYtte4xWgzK6wLM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi;\n     2→\n     3→import io.undertow.Undertow;\n     4→import io.undertow.servlet.Servlets;\n     5→import io.undertow.servlet.api.DeploymentInfo;\n     6→import org.jboss.resteasy.plugins.server.undertow.UndertowJaxrsServer;\n     7→import org.jboss.weld.environment.servlet.Listener;\n     8→\n     9→public class Main {\n    10→\n    11→  public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {\n    12→    // Initialize Hibernate EntityManagerFactory early\n    13→    org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.persistence.EntityManagerFactoryProducer.initialize();\n    14→\n    15→    UndertowJaxrsServer server = new UndertowJaxrsServer();\n    16→\n    17→    Undertow.Builder builder =\n    18→        Undertow.builder().addHttpListener(8080, \"0.0.0.0\").setWorkerThreads(50);\n    19→\n    20→    server.start(builder);\n    21→\n    22→    DeploymentInfo di =\n    23→        server\n    24→            .undertowDeployment(RestApplication.class)\n    25→            .setClassLoader(Main.class.getClassLoader())\n    26→            .setContextPath(\"/\")\n    27→            .setDeploymentName(\"RealWorldAPI\")\n    28→            .addListener(Servlets.listener(Listener.class));\n    29→\n    30→    server.deploy(di);\n    31→\n    32→    System.out.println(\"RealWorld API started on http://0.0.0.0:8080\");\n    33→    System.out.println(\"API base path: /api\");\n    34→  }\n    35→}\n    36→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"efe30994-3667-4266-9e94-a5bfae7ec80a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014DPm4kEVjFWXvgJS5ZiGx3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.persistence;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n     5→import jakarta.enterprise.inject.Produces;\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManagerFactory;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.Persistence;\n     8→\n     9→@Dependent\n    10→public class EntityManagerFactoryProducer {\n    11→\n    12→  private static volatile EntityManagerFactory emf;\n    13→\n    14→  public static void initialize() {\n    15→    if (emf == null) {\n    16→      synchronized (EntityManagerFactoryProducer.class) {\n    17→        if (emf == null) {\n    18→          emf = Persistence.createEntityManagerFactory(\"realworld\");\n    19→        }\n    20→      }\n    21→    }\n    22→  }\n    23→\n    24→  @Produces\n    25→  @ApplicationScoped\n    26→  public EntityManagerFactory createEntityManagerFactory() {\n    27→    initialize();\n    28→    return emf;\n    29→  }\n    30→}\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"0dc75265-ea29-4ba4-912d-15e3511a5ba1"}
