{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Prf2sPXAk2dRDgxtbd66qx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n     2→\n     3→USER root\n     4→# install uv and PostgreSQL\n     5→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl lsof python3-venv python3-full postgresql postgresql-client \\\n     6→    && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n     7→\n     8→ENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n     9→\n    10→# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\n    11→ENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\n    12→RUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n    13→\n    14→# create venv and install\n    15→RUN uv venv /opt/venv     && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n    16→\n    17→ENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n    18→RUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n    19→\n    20→# Set working directory\n    21→WORKDIR /app\n    22→\n    23→# Copy all the assets\n    24→COPY . .\n    25→\n    26→RUN if [ -f mvnw ]; then chmod +x mvnw; fi && if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n    27→RUN chmod +x start.sh\n    28→\n    29→# Build the application at image build time\n    30→RUN mvn clean package -DskipTests -Dmaven.test.skip=true\n    31→\n    32→CMD [\"/app/start.sh\"]\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"82b0ae47-730d-48e0-a4e3-0f79457c6ec8"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_019btKSACzNK9c1xKrFu2Hvx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Dockerfile does `COPY . .` and then `mvn clean package`. The `mvn clean` should remove old compiled classes. But the error clearly mentions `PersistenceConfiguration` which doesn't exist in our source files. The issue could be Docker layer caching. Let me rebuild with `--no-cache`. But first, let me also address the actual Jandex issue.\n\nThe real problem is that Maven Shade creates a fat JAR by unpacking all dependency JARs and merging them. If both `io.smallrye:jandex:3.2.0` and any other JAR contribute classes to `org/jboss/jandex/`, the last one wins. The Shade plugin needs explicit configuration to handle this.\n\nActually wait - looking more carefully, the `io.smallrye:jandex:3.2.0` JAR **does** contain classes in the `org.jboss.jandex` package (it's a relocation). But the error says `indexWithSummary` isn't found. This suggests the old Jandex classes are somehow overwriting the new ones in the shade JAR.\n\nThe simplest fix is to add a shade plugin `<relocations>` or filter to only include Jandex classes from the SmallRye jar. But actually, since the old jandex is excluded from the dependency tree already, the issue might be Docker caching. Let me try a `--no-cache` build:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":695,"cache_read_input_tokens":46795,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":695,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":457},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"2322a839-cf5e-4425-bcf1-f59588e22998"}
