{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01LnvjW1ebAq8fDjGM6BgSES","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The file was last modified at 15:26 but the Docker build happened at ~16:13. The file should be the correct one. \n\nActually, I bet the issue is that the summary mentions an older, more complex Main.java that was created in the first context window. But in the second context window (the resumed session), it was simplified. The file at 15:26 modification time (during the second context) has the simplified version. But Docker is somehow picking up the old complex one.\n\nLet me look at this from a different angle. The Docker image shows `EntityManagerProducer` (not `EntityManagerFactoryProducer`) in the old Main.java. This is a completely different architecture. The file in Docker must be from a git stash or overlay. \n\nInstead of debugging why Docker sees a different file, let me just embrace the situation. The Main.java in Docker is actually a more functional version that uses Weld SE directly, CdiInjectorFactory, and proper RESTEasy deployment. It's 500ing because:\n1. It references `EntityManagerProducer` which doesn't exist (we have `EntityManagerFactoryProducer`)\n2. It references old mapper classes like `ExceptionMappers` \n3. It's missing `HealthResource` from the resources list\n\nBut wait - the server DID start successfully with that Main.java! `CDI container initialized`, `JPA EntityManager ready`, `RealWorld API started on port 8080`. So it's working at the Main.java level, the 500 is something else.\n\nActually, the container DID start. So the Main.java in Docker worked. The 500 is happening at request time. The `HealthResource` is not in the `setScannedResourceClasses` list, so it returns 500 (or 404). Let me check what the old Main.java registers - it doesn't include HealthResource.\n\nRather than fighting the Docker build context issue, let me update MY local Main.java to match what Docker actually needs, making it a clean version. The Docker image's Main.java actually has a better architecture for CDI integration (using Weld SE + CdiInjectorFactory). Let me update the local file to match and fix the issues:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":511,"cache_read_input_tokens":81930,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":511,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":614},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"ce2c57d2-da02-4fca-a6db-e804d74cf1de"}
