{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016vmaho2k5ViKHzYMGLas3k","type":"tool_result","content":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/security/RolesAllowedFilter.java\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__quarkus__jakarta/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/persistence/EntityManagerProducer.java","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"bae23d42-13b1-4838-b939-2b4aecfdd6b4"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Pri1VxmxZ9wK1bRbUjSi6i","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"There ARE local versions of `EntityManagerProducer.java` and `RolesAllowedFilter.java` - but in different packages (`infrastructure.persistence` and `infrastructure.web.security`). The Docker image has EXTRA copies at the root package level. These were created in the first context window and Docker sees them.\n\nWait - but `ls` earlier showed they're not in the root package locally. Docker must be caching them from a previous build. The real problem is that Docker BuildKit is somehow reusing old COPY layers despite `--no-cache`.\n\nLet me try a completely different approach - I'll modify the Dockerfile to add a cache-busting arg:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":711,"cache_read_input_tokens":86847,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":711,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":249},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"2966be97-812d-4c51-b2b0-fc7c062ed660"}
