{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01PGRZBkyutaSXGkYM38aqPM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see the issue: `ContextBeanInstance.getInstance(ContextBeanInstance.java:86)` → `getIfExists` returns null. This happens when a `@RequestScoped` bean is accessed outside of an active request scope. The Weld SE container doesn't have a request scope active during RESTEasy's servlet invocation. The Weld Servlet integration typically handles this, but we're using Weld SE + Undertow without the Weld Servlet Listener.\n\nLet me check - the current Main.java uses `Weld` (SE) directly but doesn't use the `Listener` (Weld Servlet Listener). That's the problem. The old Main.java in the Docker image (from first context) used `Weld` directly and registered resources and providers via `setScannedResourceClasses`. But without the Weld Servlet Listener, request scoping doesn't work.\n\nI need to integrate Weld Servlet with the Undertow deployment. Let me update Main.java to add the Weld Servlet Listener:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1120,"cache_read_input_tokens":105447,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1120,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":359},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d45be86e-3e5a-4433-b76a-a33ae6e615f7","uuid":"49bb3233-717f-4176-afd9-85d584e006b7"}
